@Toc "Main"

Software and Hardware required
******************************

The following libraries (with minimum version) are required to run
@{b}TSMorph@{ub}:

     intuition.library        37
     iffparse.library         37
     graphics.library         37
     layers.library           37
     gadtools.library         37
     asl.library              37
     utility.library          37
     diskfont.library         36
     icon.library             37
     rexxsyslib.library       0

The following will also be used if present:

     amigaguide.library       34
     dctv.library             3
     opal.library             0  @{b}Note:@{ub} OpalVision board is not required
     reqtools.library         38 reqtools is ©1991/1992 Nico François
                                 This is required for Animated Warps/Morphs
     nofrag.library           2  nofrag is © Copyright 1991 Jaba Development.
     egs.library              0  EGS is © Copyright 1990/93 VIONA Development.
     egsintui.library         0
     egsgfx.library           0
     egsrequest.library       0

@{b}TSMorph-render@{ub} requires a large amount of chip memory (or
@{b}opal.library@{ub}). If you have 1Mb then 512x512 images can be morphed
(though you may have to run workbench on a 2 colour 640x200 screen).
640x512 is probably impossible without 2Mb of chip memory.

The amount of chip memory required by @{b}TSMorph@{ub} can be reduced to 1/5 by
setting the @{"ZOOM" Link "P-ZOOM"} parameter to @{b}OFF@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "Par" "TSMorph.guide/Par"
@Next "Info"
@Prev "Requirements"
@Toc "Main"

Tool types and Shell parameters
*******************************

Both @{b}TSMorph@{ub} and @{b}TSMorph-render@{ub} can be run from the Shell or the
Workbench. Most parameters can be edited using the @{"Settings" Link "men-Settings"} menu.

@{b}Note:@{ub} @{b}TSMorph@{ub} and @{b}TSMorph-render@{ub} both require a stack size of more than
4096. 8192 should be OK. If the stack is not set large enough then the
programs will probably just crash.

Parameters can be supplied, normally either on the @{b}Shell@{ub} command line,
as Icon @{b}Tool Types@{ub} on the @{b}Project@{ub}, @{b}TSMorph@{ub} or @{b}TSMorph-render@{ub} Icon, or
in a @{b}settings file@{ub}.

The format of settings files is a text file with lines in the format:

     Settingstype=settingsvalue

Blank lines or lines starting with a ; (semi-colon) are treated as
comments. Any settings supplied on the @{b}Shell@{ub} command line or as an Icon
@{b}Tool Type@{ub} override values specified in this file. Parameters on the
@{b}Project@{ub} Icon override parameters on the @{b}Tool@{ub} Icon.

@{b}Note:@{ub} All the @{b}Project@{ub} Icon tool types are used if the project is run
with a @{b}default@{ub} tool or by @{b}double clicking@{ub} a tool, some are not used if
the project is selected using a @{b}file requester@{ub}, if the Tool was run
from the @{b}Shell@{ub} then file requester selected project tool types are
ignored. Also some @{b}settings@{ub} can not be changed on @{b}open@{ub} projects,

The Settings file name used is first file found from:

     1) The name supplied in the @{b}SETTINGS=@{ub} parameter on the project.
     2) The name supplied in the @{b}SETTINGS=@{ub} parameter on the tool.
     3) @{b}TSMorph.prefs@{ub}
        in the @{b}project@{ub} directory for the @{b}workbench@{ub},
        the @{b}current@{ub} directory from the @{b}Shell@{ub}.
     4) @{b}TSMorph.prefs@{ub}
        in the directory @{b}TSMorph@{ub} was loaded from.
     5) @{b}ENV:TSMorph/TSMorph.prefs@{ub}

Unless @{"KEEPSETTINGS" Link "P-KEEPSETTINGS"} is set to @{b}NO@{ub} current settings are saved in
@{b}ENV:TSMorph/TSMorph.prefs@{ub} when @{b}TSMorph@{ub} is quit. Settings can be saved
and loaded from the @{"Settings" Link "men-Settings"} menu.


 @{" TSMorph-prefs  " Link "TSMorph-prefs"}                   Preferences editor
 @{" TSMorph        " Link "Par-TSMorph"}                   Parameters to @{b}TSMorph@{ub}
 @{" TSMorph-render " Link "Par-TSMorph-render"}                   Parameters to @{b}TSMorph-render@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "Par-TSMorph" "TSMorph.guide/Par-TSMorph"
@Next "Par-TSMorph-render"
@Toc "Par"

Parameters to @{b}TSMorph@{ub}
=====================

The following parameters can be supplied, normally either on the @{b}Shell@{ub}
command line, as Icon @{b}Tool Types@{ub} on the @{b}Project@{ub} or @{b}TSMorph@{ub} Icon, or in
a @{b}settings file@{ub}:


 @{" CHANGEPALETTE " Link "P-CHANGEPALETTE"}                Change screen palette to match image
 @{" CREATEICONS   " Link "P-CREATEICONS"}                Create project Icons
 @{" CREATEICONSP  " Link "P-CREATEICONSP"}                Create prefs Icons
 @{" CUSTOMDEPTH   " Link "P-CUSTOMDEPTH"}                Custom screen depth
 @{" CUSTOMMODE    " Link "P-CUSTOMMODE"}                Custom screen mode
 @{" EGS           " Link "P-EGS"}                Use EGS for image windows
 @{" FILES         " Link "P-FILES"}                Specify file to open
 @{" HELP          " Link "P-HELP"}                Display continuous help
 @{" KEEPSETTINGS  " Link "P-KEEPSETTINGS"}                Save settings on Quit
 @{" OPENMODE      " Link "P-OPENMODE"}                How to open images
 @{" PREVIEW       " Link "P-PREVIEW"}                ARexx script to preview image
 @{" PUBSCREEN     " Link "P-PUBSCREEN"}                Public screen to use
 @{" REQTOOLS      " Link "P-REQTOOLS"}                Use Reqtools.library?
 @{" SETTINGS      " Link "P-SETTINGS"}                Settings file name
 @{" ZOOM          " Link "P-ZOOM"}                Zoom image 2 times


@EndNode

@Node "P-CHANGEPALETTE" "TSMorph.guide/P-CHANGEPALETTE"
@Next "P-CREATEICONS"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph"

CHANGEPALETTE=YES/NO/OFF
------------------------

Sets the default value of the @{b}Change Palette?@{ub} settings menu item -
defaults to @{b}YES@{ub}.

This item toggles if each images palette should be used to display the
image when the window is active. Each image window can have its own
palette. This option operates with the @{"OPENMODE" Link "P-OPENMODE"} parameter.

Since the ability to change screens colour palettes is not supported by
CBM this menu option can be disabled by setting this parameter to @{b}OFF@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "P-CREATEICONS" "TSMorph.guide/P-CREATEICONS"
@Next "P-CREATEICONSP"
@Prev "P-CHANGEPALETTE"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph"

CREATEICONS=YES/NO
------------------

Sets the default value of the @{b}Create Icons?@{ub} settings menu item -
defaults to @{b}YES@{ub}.

This item toggles if Icons are to be saved with @{"parameter files" Link "File_Format"}. If it
is selected then an Icon will be saved. The icon will come from
@{b}ENV:TSMorph/def_points@{ub} if this exists, secondly from
@{b}ENV:SYS/def_points@{ub}, otherwise the @{b}default project Icon@{ub} is used.

This parameter is not changed by Requester loaded projects.


@EndNode

@Node "P-CREATEICONSP" "TSMorph.guide/P-CREATEICONSP"
@Next "P-CUSTOMDEPTH"
@Prev "P-CREATEICONS"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph"

CREATEICONSP=YES/NO
-------------------

Sets the default value of the @{b}Create Prefs Icons?@{ub} settings menu item -
defaults to @{b}YES@{ub}.

This item toggles if Icons are to be saved with @{"Settings" Link "Par"} files. If it is
selected then an Icon will be saved. The icon will come from
@{b}ENV:TSMorph/def_prefs@{ub} if this exists, secondly from @{b}ENV:SYS/def_prefs@{ub},
otherwise the @{b}default project Icon@{ub} is used.


@EndNode

@Node "P-CUSTOMDEPTH" "TSMorph.guide/P-CUSTOMDEPTH"
@Next "P-CUSTOMMODE"
@Prev "P-CREATEICONSP"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph"

CUSTOMDEPTH=4
-------------

This gives the depth of the custom screen to open if @{"CUSTOMMODE" Link "P-CUSTOMMODE"} is
specified.

It can be changed using the menu item (if @{b}reqtools.library@{ub} is
available), a requester is displayed allowing the input of the screen
mode, but any change is ignored until @{b}TSMorph@{ub} is reloaded.

The default value is 4.


@EndNode

@Node "P-CUSTOMMODE" "TSMorph.guide/P-CUSTOMMODE"
@Next "P-EGS"
@Prev "P-CUSTOMDEPTH"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph"

CUSTOMMODE=screen_mode
----------------------

This gives the mode of the custom screen to open.

The mode is as show in the Screen Mode requester - case is ignored
(e.g. "PAL:Low Res"). This parameter is not changed by Requester loaded
projects.

The name of the screen must be given by the @{"PUBSCREEN" Link "P-PUBSCREEN"} parameter. The
depth is given by the @{"CUSTOMDEPTH" Link "P-CUSTOMDEPTH"} parameter. The screen will mostly
clone the Workbench, but other colours will be set up as a grey scale.

It can be changed using the menu item (if @{b}reqtools.library@{ub} is
available), a requester is displayed allowing the input of the screen
mode, but any change is ignored until @{b}TSMorph@{ub} is reloaded.

The default value is nothing which means do not open a custom screen.


@EndNode

@Node "P-EGS" "TSMorph.guide/P-EGS"
@Next "P-FILES"
@Prev "P-CUSTOMMODE"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph"

EGS=YES/NO
----------

This controls the use of @{b}EGS@{ub} when displaying the @{"edit" Link "Edit"} windows. See
@{"requirements" Link "Requirements"} for library requirements. If set to yes then the @{"edit" Link "Edit"}
windows and relevent @{"error" Link "Req-Error"} requesters are displayed on the default @{b}EGS@{ub}
screen.

@{"ZOOM" Link "P-ZOOM"} is always set to @{b}OFF@{ub} when using @{b}EGS@{ub}. @{"OPENMODE" Link "P-OPENMODE"} may also be ignored
in some circumstances.

This parameter is not available as a menu option, is not saved in
settings files and can not be specified on a project Icon.

Default values is @{b}NO@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "P-FILES" "TSMorph.guide/P-FILES"
@Next "P-HELP"
@Prev "P-EGS"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph"

FILES=filename
--------------

This is only relevant to the @{b}Shell@{ub}, only one name can be supplied -
default is to open a new unnamed project.


@EndNode

@Node "P-HELP" "TSMorph.guide/P-HELP"
@Next "P-KEEPSETTINGS"
@Prev "P-FILES"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph"

HELP=YES/NO
-----------

Sets the default value of the @{b}Continuous Help?@{ub} settings menu item -
defaults to @{b}NO@{ub}.

This option has more effect when running release 3.0 or later. When set
to @{b}YES@{ub} help is continuously displayed using amigaguide (if available).


@EndNode

@Node "P-KEEPSETTINGS" "TSMorph.guide/P-KEEPSETTINGS"
@Next "P-OPENMODE"
@Prev "P-HELP"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph"

KEEPSETTINGS=YES/NO
-------------------

Sets the default value of the @{b}Keep Settings?@{ub} settings menu item -
defaults to @{b}YES@{ub}.

By default current settings are saved in @{b}ENV:TSMorph/TSMorph.prefs@{ub} when
@{b}TSMorph@{ub} is @{b}quit@{ub}. This parameter and menu item enable this behaviour to
be turned off.


@EndNode

@Node "P-OPENMODE" "TSMorph.guide/P-OPENMODE"
@Next "P-PREVIEW"
@Prev "P-KEEPSETTINGS"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph"

OPENMODE=ALWAYS/IFILBM/IFCOLOURS/REMAP/OPAL
-------------------------------------------

This parameter and menu item specify how images should be loaded for
displaying by @{b}TSMorph@{ub}.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}ALWAYS@{ub}    - Only try and load normal ILBM images. Fail if not.
     The @{"CHANGEPALETTE" Link "P-CHANGEPALETTE"} parameter has an affect on the image display.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}IFILBM@{ub}    - First try to load as an ILBM image, load and remap
     the image if the image is not an ILBM or has 24 planes.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}IFCOLOURS@{ub} - As @{b}IFILBM@{ub} but remap if the number of planes in the
     image exceed the number of the screen.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}REMAP@{ub}     - Loads most ILBM (including 24 bit, EHB, HAM6, HAM8
     and DCTV (with @{b}dctv.library@{ub} [@{b}REMAP@{ub} needs to be specified to
     correctly display DCTV images]), JPEG, TARGA, PPM and GIF. For
     JPEG if @{"CHANGEPALETTE=YES or NO" Link "P-CHANGEPALETTE"} and the screen (see @{"PUBSCREEN" Link "P-PUBSCREEN"}) has
     more than 2 bit planes then the image is remapped to a dynamic
     type @{"palette" Link "P-CHANGEPALETTE"}. Otherwise the image is remapped to the screen
     palette. If this fails then @{b}opal.library@{ub} will be used (if
     present). This may be required for some JPEGs.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}OPAL@{ub}      - Always use @{b}opal.library@{ub} to load the image. This is
     probably only useful to load images in Opal FAST IFF format.  The
     images are remapped to the current palette.

When loading and remapping complex images a requester is displayed with
a title of @{b}Loading Image@{ub}, a text gadget giving progress messages, a
Pass gadget, and a third progress gadget. There is @{b}no way@{ub} of
interrupting the load process.

For slow machines it is suggested that you convert the images to ILBMs
and specify @{b}ALWAYS@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "P-PREVIEW" "TSMorph.guide/P-PREVIEW"
@Next "P-PUBSCREEN"
@Prev "P-OPENMODE"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph"

PREVIEW=scriptname
------------------

This specifies the name of an @{"ARexx" Link "AR-Preview"} script to run to preview the
rendered image.

The default script is @{"Rexx/Preview" ALINK "Rexx/Preview.TSM/Main"}.

The version supplied renders the image as a 16 colour grey scale with a
resolution of about 128/64 and displays it.

It can be changed using the menu item (if @{b}reqtools.library@{ub} is
available), a requester is displayed allowing the input of the value.


@EndNode

@Node "P-PUBSCREEN" "TSMorph.guide/P-PUBSCREEN"
@Next "P-REQTOOLS"
@Prev "P-PREVIEW"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph"

PUBSCREEN=pubscreenname
-----------------------

This gives the name of the Public Screen on which to open all @{b}TSMorph@{ub}
windows - default is the default public screen.

This parameter is not changed by Requester loaded projects.

It can be changed using the menu item (if @{b}reqtools.library@{ub} is
available), a requester is displayed allowing the input of the screen
name, but any change is ignored until @{b}TSMorph@{ub} is reloaded.

If @{"CUSTOMMODE" Link "P-CUSTOMMODE"} is supplied as well then a public screen of this name is
opened.


@EndNode

@Node "P-REQTOOLS" "TSMorph.guide/P-REQTOOLS"
@Next "P-SETTINGS"
@Prev "P-PUBSCREEN"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph"

REQTOOLS=YES/NO/ALL
-------------------

This controls the use of @{b}reqtools.library@{ub}. If set to @{b}NO@{ub} then reqtools
will not be used (except in very unusual circumstances). It will still
however be opened and closed. If set to @{b}YES@{ub} then reqtools will be used
for various requesters. If set to @{b}ALL@{ub} then it will be used for the File
Requesters as well.

This parameter is not available as a menu option, is not saved in
settings files and can not be specified on a project Icon.

Default values is @{b}YES@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "P-SETTINGS" "TSMorph.guide/P-SETTINGS"
@Next "P-ZOOM"
@Prev "P-REQTOOLS"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph"

SETTINGS=filename
-----------------

This can only be supplied on the @{b}Shell@{ub} command line, or an Icon @{b}Tool
Type@{ub}. It specifies the name of a file for more parameters. See
@{"parameters" Link "Par"}.

This parameter is not changed by Requester loaded projects.


@EndNode

@Node "P-ZOOM" "TSMorph.guide/P-ZOOM"
@Prev "P-SETTINGS"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph"

ZOOM=YES/NO/OFF
---------------

Sets the default value of the @{b}Zoom?@{ub} settings menu item. If set to @{b}YES@{ub}
then images will be initially displayed 2x normal size, if set to @{b}NO@{ub}
then images will be initially displayed normal size, setting to @{b}OFF@{ub}
disables the @{b}Zoom?@{ub} option, this reduces chip memory usage to 1/5 -
defaults to @{b}NO@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "Par-TSMorph-render" "TSMorph.guide/Par-TSMorph-render"
@Prev "Par-TSMorph"
@Toc "Par"

Parameters to @{b}TSMorph-render@{ub}
============================

The following parameters can be supplied, normally either on the @{b}Shell@{ub}
command line, as Icon @{b}Tool Types@{ub} on the @{b}Project@{ub} or @{b}TSMorph-render@{ub} Icon,
or in a @{b}settings file@{ub}:


 @{" ANTIALIAS    " Link "P-ANTIALIAS"}               Anti-Alias the output files
 @{" CREATEICONSR " Link "P-CREATEICONSR"}               Create image Icons
 @{" DEPTH        " Link "P-DEPTH"}               Depth for search algorithm
 @{" DX           " Link "P-DX"}               Horizontal Pixelation
 @{" DY           " Link "P-DY"}               Vertical Pixelation
 @{" EGS          " Link "P-EGS-R"}               Render to EGS window as well
 @{" FILES        " Link "P-FILES-R"}               Specify file to open
 @{" INTEGER      " Link "P-INTEGER"}               Integer render calculation
 @{" LOADSCRIPT   " Link "P-LOADSCRIPT"}               Script before each image loaded
 @{" MODE         " Link "P-MODE"}               Mode for rendering algorithm
 @{" POSTSCRIPT   " Link "P-POSTSCRIPT"}               Script after rendering frame
 @{" PRESCRIPT    " Link "P-PRESCRIPT"}               Script before rendering frame
 @{" PUBSCREENR   " Link "P-PUBSCREENR"}               Public screen to use
 @{" QUALITY      " Link "P-QUALITY"}               JPEG Quality
 @{" REQTOOLS     " Link "P-REQTOOLS-R"}               Use Reqtools.library?
 @{" SAVEFORMAT   " Link "P-SAVEFORMAT"}               Format to save images
 @{" SETTINGS     " Link "P-SETTINGS-R"}               Settings file name
 @{" TOOLPRI      " Link "P-TOOLPRI"}               Priority of @{b}TSMorph-render@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "P-ANTIALIAS" "TSMorph.guide/P-ANTIALIAS"
@Next "P-CREATEICONSR"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph-render"

ANTIALIAS=NO/YES
----------------

This parameter and menu item select if the output files should be
Anti-Aliased. Setting to @{b}YES@{ub} can improve the quality of the images but
will slow down the rendering process.

This parameter is ignored if @{"INTEGER" Link "P-INTEGER"} is set to @{b}YES@{ub}.

Default value is @{b}NO@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "P-CREATEICONSR" "TSMorph.guide/P-CREATEICONSR"
@Next "P-DEPTH"
@Prev "P-ANTIALIAS"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph-render"

CREATEICONSR=NO/YES
-------------------

This parameter and menu item selects if Icons are to be saved with
image files. If it is @{b}YES@{ub} then an Icon will be saved. The icon depends
on the @{"save format" Link "P-SAVEFORMAT"}.

     @{b}ENV:TSMorph/def_bw16@{ub}  - 16 colour grey scale images
     @{b}ENV:TSMorph/def_bw256@{ub} - 256 colour grey scale images
     @{b}ENV:TSMorph/def_ham6@{ub}  - HAM 6 images
     @{b}ENV:TSMorph/def_ham8@{ub}  - HAM 8 images
     @{b}ENV:TSMorph/def_dctv3@{ub} - DCTV 3 plane images using @{b}dctv.library@{ub}
     @{b}ENV:TSMorph/def_dctv4@{ub} - DCTV 4 plane images using @{b}dctv.library@{ub}
     @{b}ENV:TSMorph/def_iff@{ub}   - 24 bit ILBM saved using @{b}opal.library@{ub}
     @{b}ENV:TSMorph/def_ilbm@{ub}  - 24 bit ILBM saved without @{b}opal.library@{ub}
     @{b}ENV:TSMorph/def_jpg@{ub}   - JPEG files saved using @{b}opal.library@{ub}
     @{b}ENV:TSMorph/def_ppm@{ub}   - PPM files

If the file does not exist then @{b}ENV:SYS/def_ilbm@{ub} (etc.) is tried, if
this does not exist then the @{b}default project Icon@{ub} is used.

Default value is NO.


@EndNode

@Node "P-DEPTH" "TSMorph.guide/P-DEPTH"
@Next "P-DX"
@Prev "P-CREATEICONSR"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph-render"

DEPTH=number
------------

This parameter indicates how deep the Morphing @{"algorithm" Link "Algorithms"} should search
to find the points to use for morphing. The maximum value is 20 (higher
values are accepted but will be taken as 20).

Default value is @{b}2@{ub}.

It can be changed using the menu item (if @{b}reqtools.library@{ub} is
available), a requester is displayed allowing the input of the value.


@EndNode

@Node "P-DX" "TSMorph.guide/P-DX"
@Next "P-DY"
@Prev "P-DEPTH"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph-render"

DX=number
---------

This parameter can be used to speed up the rendering process. The
default value is @{b}0@{ub}.

If set to a number then only some Horizontal pixels will be generated.
e.g. if set to @{b}3@{ub} then only every 4th pixel will be generated. The
others will be copied from the previous pixel. This can be overridden
by using @{"ARexx" Link "AR-Prescript"}. Also see @{"DY" Link "P-DY"}.

It can be changed using the menu item (if @{b}reqtools.library@{ub} is
available), a requester is displayed allowing the input of the value.


@EndNode

@Node "P-DY" "TSMorph.guide/P-DY"
@Next "P-EGS-R"
@Prev "P-DX"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph-render"

DY=number
---------

This parameter can be used to speed up the rendering process. The
default value is @{b}0@{ub}.

If set to a number then only some Vertical pixels will be generated.
e.g. if set to @{b}1@{ub} then only every other line will be generated. The
others will be copied from the previous line. This can be overridden by
using @{"ARexx" Link "AR-Prescript"}. Also see @{"DX" Link "P-DX"}.

It can be changed using the menu item (if @{b}reqtools.library@{ub} is
available), a requester is displayed allowing the input of the value.


@EndNode

@Node "P-EGS-R" "TSMorph.guide/P-EGS-R"
@Next "P-FILES-R"
@Prev "P-DY"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph-render"

EGS=YES/NO
----------

By default @{b}TSMorph-render@{ub} does not show its output when rendering. If
this parameter is set to @{b}YES@{ub} then output will be displayed in an @{b}EGS@{ub}
window on the default @{b}EGS@{ub} screen a line at a time. See @{"requirements" Link "Requirements"} for
library requirements.

This parameter is not available as a menu option, is not saved in
settings files and can not be specified on a project Icon.

Default values is @{b}NO@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "P-FILES-R" "TSMorph.guide/P-FILES-R"
@Next "P-INTEGER"
@Prev "P-EGS-R"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph-render"

FILES=filename
--------------

This is only relevant to the @{b}Shell@{ub}, only one name can be supplied -
default is to show an ASL file requester for the file to run.


@EndNode

@Node "P-INTEGER" "TSMorph.guide/P-INTEGER"
@Next "P-LOADSCRIPT"
@Prev "P-FILES-R"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph-render"

INTEGER=NO/YES
--------------

This parameter and menu item select if the render process should use
integer or floating point arithmetic. The process will be faster if
integer arithmetic is used (especially on machines without an FPU).
However the output quality will not be so good.

If this parameter is set to @{b}YES@{ub} then the @{"ANTIALIAS" Link "P-ANTIALIAS"} parameter is ignored.

Default value is @{b}NO@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "P-LOADSCRIPT" "TSMorph.guide/P-LOADSCRIPT"
@Next "P-MODE"
@Prev "P-INTEGER"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph-render"

LOADSCRIPT=Scriptname/OFF
-------------------------

This specifies the name of an @{"ARexx" Link "AR-Loadscript"} script to run before each image 24
bit image is loaded. This can be used to e.g. hold the images on disc
in JPEG format to save space and convert each image back to 24 bit ILBM
when required. Note however that @{b}TSMorph-render@{ub} now has the ability to
load a large variety of image formats (All ILBM including HAM6, HAM8,
EHB, and DCTV with @{b}dctv.library@{ub}, JPEG, TARGA, PPM, and GIF).

The default script is @{"Rexx/Loadscript" ALINK
"Rexx/Loadscript.TSM/Main"}.

The version supplied does nothing.

Set to @{b}OFF@{ub} to run no script.

It can be changed using the menu item (if @{b}reqtools.library@{ub} is
available), a requester is displayed allowing the input of the value.


@EndNode

@Node "P-MODE" "TSMorph.guide/P-MODE"
@Next "P-POSTSCRIPT"
@Prev "P-LOADSCRIPT"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph-render"

MODE=0-31
---------

This parameter and menu item indicate how the Morphing @{"algorithm" Link "Algorithms"} should
search to find the points to use for morphing.

The values are additive:
        @{b}1@{ub} : Leaves un-triangled point stationary
        @{b}2@{ub} : Searches all the closest points
        @{b}4@{ub} : Uses a squaring algorithm to find close points
        @{b}8@{ub} : Uses a Delaunay algorithm to find triangles
        @{b}16@{ub}: Precalculate close points

Default value is @{b}0@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "P-POSTSCRIPT" "TSMorph.guide/P-POSTSCRIPT"
@Next "P-PRESCRIPT"
@Prev "P-MODE"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph-render"

POSTSCRIPT=Scriptname/OFF
-------------------------

This specifies the name of an @{"ARexx" Link "AR-Prescript"} script to run after each image is
rendered. This can be used to build an animation or change the image
format from 24 bit.

The default script is @{"Rexx/Postscript" ALINK
"Rexx/Postscript.TSM/Main"}.

The version supplied does nothing.

Set to @{b}OFF@{ub} to run no script.

It can be changed using the menu item (if @{b}reqtools.library@{ub} is
available), a requester is displayed allowing the input of the value.


@EndNode

@Node "P-PRESCRIPT" "TSMorph.guide/P-PRESCRIPT"
@Next "P-PUBSCREENR"
@Prev "P-POSTSCRIPT"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph-render"

PRESCRIPT=Scriptname/OFF
------------------------

This specifies the name of an @{"ARexx" Link "AR-Prescript"} script to run before each image is
rendered. This can be used to produce only some of the frames and
control the movement and colour of the images.

The default script is @{"Rexx/Prescript" ALINK
"Rexx/Prescript.TSM/Main"}.

The version supplied does nothing.

Set to @{b}OFF@{ub} to run no script.

It can be changed using the menu item (if @{b}reqtools.library@{ub} is
available), a requester is displayed allowing the input of the value.


@EndNode

@Node "P-PUBSCREENR" "TSMorph.guide/P-PUBSCREENR"
@Next "P-QUALITY"
@Prev "P-PRESCRIPT"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph-render"

PUBSCREENR=pubscreenname
------------------------

This gives the name of the Public Screen on which to open
@{b}TSMorph-render@{ub} windows - default is the default public screen.

It can be changed using the menu item (if @{b}reqtools.library@{ub} is
available), a requester is displayed allowing the input of the screen
name.


@EndNode

@Node "P-QUALITY" "TSMorph.guide/P-QUALITY"
@Next "P-REQTOOLS-R"
@Prev "P-PUBSCREENR"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph-render"

QUALITY=number
--------------

This specifies the quality of output files. This option only applies if
@{b}opal.library@{ub} is available and @{"SAVEFORMAT" Link "P-SAVEFORMAT"} is @{b}JPEG@{ub} or @{b}JPEGT@{ub}. Possible
values are @{b}0@{ub} to @{b}100@{ub}.

Default value is @{b}75@{ub}.

It can be changed using the menu item (if @{b}reqtools.library@{ub} is
available), a requester is displayed allowing the input of the value.


@EndNode

@Node "P-REQTOOLS-R" "TSMorph.guide/P-REQTOOLS-R"
@Next "P-SAVEFORMAT"
@Prev "P-QUALITY"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph-render"

REQTOOLS=YES/NO/ALL
-------------------

This controls the use of @{b}reqtools.library@{ub}. If set to @{b}NO@{ub} then reqtools
will not be used (except in very unusual circumstances). It will still
however be opened and closed. If set to @{b}YES@{ub} then reqtools will be used
for various requesters. If set to @{b}ALL@{ub} then it will be used for the File
Requesters as well.

This parameter is not available as a menu option, is not saved in
settings files and can not be specified on a project Icon.

Default values is @{b}YES@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "P-SAVEFORMAT" "TSMorph.guide/P-SAVEFORMAT"
@Next "P-SETTINGS-R"
@Prev "P-REQTOOLS-R"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph-render"

SAVEFORMAT=ILBM24/OPAL24/OPAL24T/OPAL24F/OPAL24FT/JPEG/JPEGT/PPM/BW16/BW256/HAM6/HAM8/DCTV3/DCTV4
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This parameter and menu item specify the format @{b}TSMorph-render@{ub} should
use to save the output images. @{b}OPAL@{ub} and @{b}JPEG@{ub} formats are only available
if @{b}opal.library@{ub} is available. @{b}DCTV3@{ub} and @{b}DCTV4@{ub} formats are only
available if @{b}dctv.library@{ub} is available.

     @{b}ILBM24@{ub}   - IFF 24 bit ILBM with no CAMG chunk
     @{b}OPAL24@{ub}   - IFF 24 bit ILBM saved using @{b}opal.library@{ub}
     @{b}OPAL24T@{ub}  - as @{b}OPAL24@{ub} with a Thumbnail
     @{b}OPAL24F@{ub}  - as @{b}OPAL24@{ub} in Fast Format
     @{b}OPAL24TF@{ub} - as @{b}OPAL24F@{ub} with a Thumbnail
     @{b}JPEG@{ub}     - JPEG format using @{b}opal.library@{ub}
     @{b}JPEGT@{ub}    - as @{b}JPEG@{ub} with a Thumbnail
     @{b}PPM@{ub}      - PPM format
     @{b}BW16@{ub}     - ILBM 16 colour grey scale
     @{b}BW256@{ub}    - ILBM 256 colour grey scale
     @{b}HAM6@{ub}     - ILBM 6 plane HAM
     @{b}HAM8@{ub}     - ILBM 8 plane HAM
     @{b}DCTV3@{ub}    - ILBM 3 plane DCTV using @{b}dctv.library@{ub}
     @{b}DCTV4@{ub}    - ILBM 4 plane DCTV using @{b}dctv.library@{ub}

The quality of JPEG images can be set using the @{"QUALITY" Link "P-QUALITY"} parameter.

PPM format is basically uncompressed 24 bit. The files are therefore
very large and it is suggested that a compressing file handler (such as
XFH or EPU) is used. This format is provided mainly to allow the easy
production of MPEG movies.

The save format also controls which @{"Icon" Link "P-CREATEICONSR"} is saved with the image.


@EndNode

@Node "P-SETTINGS-R" "TSMorph.guide/P-SETTINGS-R"
@Next "P-TOOLPRI"
@Prev "P-SAVEFORMAT"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph-render"

SETTINGS=filename
-----------------

This can only be supplied on the @{b}Shell@{ub} command line, or an Icon @{b}Tool
Type@{ub}.

This specifies the name of a file to contain settings.  See @{"parameters" Link "Par"}.


@EndNode

@Node "P-TOOLPRI" "TSMorph.guide/P-TOOLPRI"
@Prev "P-SETTINGS-R"
@Toc "Par-TSMorph-render"

TOOLPRI=number
--------------

This can only be supplied as a @{b}Tool@{ub} Icon tool type. It sets the
priority of the rendering process.

Setting to @{b}-1@{ub} is a good idea if you wish to run the program in the
background. The default value is @{b}0@{ub}. Setting to positive values is
generally @{b}not@{ub} a good idea.


@EndNode

@Node "Info" "TSMorph.guide/Info"
@Next "Con"
@Prev "Par"
@Toc "Main"

The Information Window
**********************

This window is always displayed when @{b}TSMorph@{ub} is running. It displays
information about the current project. The window title is @{b}TSMorph@{ub}, the
screen title will be displayed as the project name if the project has a
name. It is used to set up all the information required by
@{b}TSMorph-render@{ub}.


 @{" Gadgets  " Link "I-gad"}      Gadgets displayed in the Info Window
 @{" Menus    " Link "I-men"}      Menus available in the Info Window
 @{" Keyboard " Link "I-Key"}      Keyboard controls in the Info Window


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad" "TSMorph.guide/I-gad"
@Next "I-men"
@Toc "Info"

Gadgets in Info Window
======================

@font topaz.font 8

The Information Window appears with gadgets:

     ----------------------------
     |@{"." Link "I-gad-Close"}|TSMorph            |@{" " Link "I-gad-Zoom"}|@{" " Link "I-gad-Depth"}|
     |--------------------------|
     |@{"        Help Text         " Link "I-gad-Help"}|
     | File @{u}O@{uu}ne @{"............." Link "I-gad-File_One"} @{"X" Link "I-gad-Get_File_One"}|
     | File @{u}T@{uu}wo @{"............." Link "I-gad-File_One"} @{"X" Link "I-gad-Get_File_Two"}|
     |24 File @{u}1@{uu} @{"............." Link "I-gad-24_File_1"} @{"X" Link "I-gad-Get_24_File_1"}|
     |24 File @{u}2@{uu} @{"............." Link "I-gad-24_File_2"} @{"X" Link "I-gad-Get_24_File_2"}|
     |    Width @{"..." Link "I-gad-Width"}  Height @{"..." Link "I-gad-Height"}|
     | @{"Single" Link "I-gad-Single"} @{u}F@{uu}rames@{".." Link "I-gad-Frames"} St@{u}a@{uu}rt @{".." Link "I-gad-Start"}|
     |     @{u}N@{uu}ame @{"............" Link "I-gad-Name"}  @{"X" Link "I-gad-Get_Name"}|
     |@{"      Edit Points...      " Link "I-gad-Edit_Points"}|
     ----------------------------


 @{" Help Text      " Link "I-gad-Help"}                    Displays help messages (release 3.0+)
 @{" File One       " Link "I-gad-File_One"}                    The first image file for point editing
 @{" Get file       " Link "I-gad-Get_File_One"}                    Get file gadget for above
 @{" File Two       " Link "I-gad-File_Two"}                    The second image file for point editing
 @{" Get File       " Link "I-gad-Get_File_Two"}                    Get file gadget for above
 @{" 24 File 1      " Link "I-gad-24_File_1"}                    The first 24 bit image file to morph
 @{" Get File       " Link "I-gad-Get_24_File_1"}                    Get file gadget for above
 @{" 24 File 2      " Link "I-gad-24_File_2"}                    The second 24 bit image file to morph
 @{" Get File       " Link "I-gad-Get_24_File_2"}                    Get file gadget for above
 @{" Width          " Link "I-gad-Width"}                    Read only gadget showing width
 @{" Height         " Link "I-gad-Height"}                    Read only gadget showing Height
 @{" Single         " Link "I-gad-Single"}                    Cycle morph mode gadget
 @{" Frames         " Link "I-gad-Frames"}                    Number of frames to generate
 @{" Start          " Link "I-gad-Start"}                    Frame number to start at
 @{" Name           " Link "I-gad-Name"}                    File name of animation frames
 @{" Get File       " Link "I-gad-Get_Name"}                    Get file gadget for above
 @{" Edit Points... " Link "I-gad-Edit_Points"}                    Display images to edit points

 @{" Close gadget   " Link "I-gad-Close"}                    Quit program
 @{" Zoom gadget    " Link "I-gad-Zoom"}                    Standard zoom window
 @{" Depth gadget   " Link "I-gad-Depth"}                    Standard depth gadget


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Help" "TSMorph.guide/I-gad-Help"
@Next "I-gad-File_One"
@Toc "I-gad"

Help Text gadget
----------------

This gadget displays short help messages.

From release 3.0 and up it displays more information. See also
@{"Continuous Help" Link "P-HELP"}.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-File_One" "TSMorph.guide/I-gad-File_One"
@Next "I-gad-Get_File_One"
@Prev "I-gad-Help"
@Toc "I-gad"

File One gadget
---------------

This gadget allows the editing of the file name of the first image to
be used when editing points. This gadget is disabled if the
@{"Edit Windows" Link "Edit"} are currently open. The file name can be either edited in
the string gadget or by using the @{"Get File" Link "I-gad-Get_File_One"} to display an ASL file
requester.

This image should be a Workbench displayable version of the
@{"first 24 bit file" Link "I-gad-24_File_1"}. (See @{"OPENMODE" Link "P-OPENMODE"} for what images can be loaded.) It is
displayed in the first @{"Edit Window" Link "Edit"} when editing points.

@{b}o@{ub} can be used to activate this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.

See @{"File naming" Link "File_Names"} for how to specify the file name.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Get_File_One" "TSMorph.guide/I-gad-Get_File_One"
@Next "I-gad-File_Two"
@Prev "I-gad-File_One"
@Toc "I-gad"

Get File One gadget
-------------------

This gadget displays an ASL file requester to select the file to appear
in the @{"File One" Link "I-gad-File_One"} gadget.

@{b}o@{ub} with @{b}shift@{ub} is the same as using this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-File_Two" "TSMorph.guide/I-gad-File_Two"
@Next "I-gad-Get_File_Two"
@Prev "I-gad-Get_File_One"
@Toc "I-gad"

File Two gadget
---------------

This gadget is the same as the @{"File One" Link "I-gad-File_One"} gadget for the second
displayable image. This image should be the same size as the first.

@{b}t@{ub} can be used to activate this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.

See @{"File naming" Link "File_Names"} for how to specify the file name.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Get_File_Two" "TSMorph.guide/I-gad-Get_File_Two"
@Next "I-gad-24_File_1"
@Prev "I-gad-File_Two"
@Toc "I-gad"

Get File Two gadget
-------------------

This gadget displays an ASL file requester to select the file to appear
in the @{"File Two" Link "I-gad-File_Two"} gadget.

@{b}t@{ub} with @{b}shift@{ub} is the same as using this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-24_File_1" "TSMorph.guide/I-gad-24_File_1"
@Next "I-gad-Get_24_File_1"
@Prev "I-gad-Get_File_Two"
@Toc "I-gad"

24 File 1 gadget
----------------

This gadget allows the editing of the file name of the first image to
be used when morphing. The file name can be either edited in the string
gadget or by using the @{"Get File" Link "I-gad-Get_24_File_1"} to display an ASL file requester.

This image should be a 24 bit version of the @{"first displayable file" Link "I-gad-File_One"}.
Also see the @{"LOADSCRIPT" Link "P-LOADSCRIPT"} parameter. Note: @{b}TSMorph@{ub} now has the ability to
load a large variety of images as 24 bit files. If this gadget is left
blank then the name from the @{"first displayable file" Link "I-gad-File_One"} is used.

@{b}1@{ub} can be used to activate this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.

See @{"File naming" Link "File_Names"} for how to specify the file name.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Get_24_File_1" "TSMorph.guide/I-gad-Get_24_File_1"
@Next "I-gad-24_File_2"
@Prev "I-gad-24_File_1"
@Toc "I-gad"

Get 24 File 1 gadget
--------------------

This gadget displays an ASL file requester to select the file to appear
in the @{"24 File 1" Link "I-gad-24_File_1"} gadget.

@{b}1@{ub} with @{b}shift@{ub} is the same as using this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-24_File_2" "TSMorph.guide/I-gad-24_File_2"
@Next "I-gad-Get_24_File_2"
@Prev "I-gad-Get_24_File_1"
@Toc "I-gad"

24 File 2 gadget
----------------

This gadget allows the editing of the file name of the last image to be
used when morphing. The file name can be either edited in the string
gadget or by using the @{"Get File" Link "I-gad-Get_24_File_2"} to display an ASL file requester.

This image should be a 24 bit version of the @{"second displayable file" Link "I-gad-File_Two"}.
Also see the @{"LOADSCRIPT" Link "P-LOADSCRIPT"} parameter. Note: @{b}TSMorph@{ub} now has the ability to
load a large variety of images as 24 bit files. If this gadget is left
blank then the name from the @{"second displayable file" Link "I-gad-File_Two"} is used.

If @{"Single Image" Link "I-gad-Single"} mode is selected then this is ignored.

@{b}2@{ub} can be used to activate this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.

See @{"File naming" Link "File_Names"} for how to specify the file name.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Get_24_File_2" "TSMorph.guide/I-gad-Get_24_File_2"
@Next "I-gad-Width"
@Prev "I-gad-24_File_2"
@Toc "I-gad"

Get 24 File 2 gadget
--------------------

This gadget displays an ASL file requester to select the file to appear
in the @{"24 File 2" Link "I-gad-24_File_2"} gadget.

@{b}2@{ub} with @{b}shift@{ub} is the same as using this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Width" "TSMorph.guide/I-gad-Width"
@Next "I-gad-Height"
@Prev "I-gad-Get_24_File_2"
@Toc "I-gad"

Width gadget
------------

This gadget displays the width of the images being edited. If images
have not been selected then it should display the maximum width of the
current points.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Height" "TSMorph.guide/I-gad-Height"
@Next "I-gad-Single"
@Prev "I-gad-Width"
@Toc "I-gad"

Height gadget
-------------

This gadget displays the height of the images being edited. If images
have not been selected then it should display the maximum height of the
current points.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Single" "TSMorph.guide/I-gad-Single"
@Next "I-gad-Frames"
@Prev "I-gad-Height"
@Toc "I-gad"

Single image gadget
-------------------

This gadget cycles between @{b}Morphs@{ub}, @{b}Warps@{ub}, @{b}Animated Morphs@{ub} and @{b}Animated
Warps@{ub}.

In @{b}Warp@{ub} mode one image is distorted based on the control points.

In @{b}Morph@{ub} mode one image is distorted/recoloured into a second image
based on control points.

In @{b}animated Warps@{ub} and @{b}Morphs@{ub} the input images can change on each output
frame.

@{b}r@{ub} and @{b}R@{ub} can be used to cycle this gadget forward and backward - See
@{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.

@{b}Note:@{ub} @{b}Animated Warps/Morphs@{ub} are only available if @{b}Reqtools@{ub} is available.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Frames" "TSMorph.guide/I-gad-Frames"
@Next "I-gad-Start"
@Prev "I-gad-Single"
@Toc "I-gad"

Number of Frames gadget
-----------------------

This gadget can be used to specify the number of frames to generate.

In @{"Single" Link "I-gad-Single"} mode the total number of frames will be this number plus the
first image.

In dual mode the total number of frames is the first image, this number
and the last image.

@{b}f@{ub} can be used to activate this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.

This gadget is disabled if Images are displayed and an @{b}animated
Morph/Warp@{ub} is being edited.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Start" "TSMorph.guide/I-gad-Start"
@Next "I-gad-Name"
@Prev "I-gad-Frames"
@Toc "I-gad"

Start Frame gadget
------------------

This gadget can be used to specify the number to use in the @{"Name" Link "I-gad-Name"} of the
first generated file. This number is then incremented by 1 for each
subsequent frame.

@{b}a@{ub} can be used to activate this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.

This gadget is disabled if Images are displayed and an @{b}animated
Morph/Warp@{ub} is being edited.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Name" "TSMorph.guide/I-gad-Name"
@Next "I-gad-Get_Name"
@Prev "I-gad-Start"
@Toc "I-gad"

Anim file Name gadget
---------------------

This gadget is used to name the files produced by @{b}TSMorph-render@{ub}.

The file name can be either edited in the string gadget or by using the
@{"Get File" Link "I-gad-Get_Name"} to display an ASL file requester.

The file name should contain the characters @{b}%ld@{ub}. These characters will
be replaced by the frame number, starting from that specified in the
@{"Start" Link "I-gad-Start"} gadget.

@{b}n@{ub} can be used to activate this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.

See @{"File naming" Link "File_Names"} for further information on how to specify the file name.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Get_Name" "TSMorph.guide/I-gad-Get_Name"
@Next "I-gad-Edit_Points"
@Prev "I-gad-Name"
@Toc "I-gad"

Get Anim file Name gadget
-------------------------

This gadget displays an ASL file requester to select the file to appear
in the @{"Name" Link "I-gad-Name"} gadget.

@{b}n@{ub} with @{b}shift@{ub} is the same as using this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Edit_Points" "TSMorph.guide/I-gad-Edit_Points"
@Next "I-gad-Close"
@Prev "I-gad-Get_Name"
@Toc "I-gad"

Edit Points... gadget
---------------------

This button gadget has the same effect as the @{"Edit Points" Link "I-men-P-Edit_Points"} menu option.
It opens the @{"Control Window" Link "Con"} and @{"Edit Windows" Link "Edit"} to allow editing of the
control points. If these windows are already open then the Control
Window is activated.

@{b}p@{ub} is the same as using this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Close" "TSMorph.guide/I-gad-Close"
@Next "I-gad-Zoom"
@Prev "I-gad-Edit_Points"
@Toc "I-gad"

Close gadget
------------

This is a standard close gadget. Clicking quits the program.

If the current project has been changed but not saved then the
@{"Unsaved Project requester" Link "Req-Unsaved"} is displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Zoom" "TSMorph.guide/I-gad-Zoom"
@Next "I-gad-Depth"
@Prev "I-gad-Close"
@Toc "I-gad"

Zoom gadget
-----------

This is a standard Zoom gadget which switches the window between full
size and a title bar and the help text.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Depth" "TSMorph.guide/I-gad-Depth"
@Prev "I-gad-Zoom"
@Toc "I-gad"

Depth gadget
------------

This is a standard depth gadget.


@EndNode

