@EndNode

@Node "I-men-P-Quit" "TSMorph.guide/I-men-P-Quit"
@Next "I-men-P-Preview"
@Prev "I-men-P-About"
@Toc "I-men-P"

Info Window Project/Quit menu item
..................................

This quits @{b}TSMorph@{ub}.

If the current project has been changed but not saved then the
@{"Unsaved Project requester" Link "Req-Unsaved"} is displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "I-men-P-Preview" "TSMorph.guide/I-men-P-Preview"
@Next "I-men-P-Edit_Points"
@Prev "I-men-P-Quit"
@Toc "I-men-P"

Info Window Project/Preview... menu item
........................................

This menu item renders the image using the ARexx script supplied in the
@{"PREVIEW" Link "P-PREVIEW"} parameter.

If required it first displays the @{"Frame Number" Link "Req-FrameNumber"} requester.

This menu option is only available if @{b}reqtools.library@{ub} is available.

If the current project has been changed but not saved then the
@{"Unsaved Project requester" Link "Req-Unsaved"} is displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "I-men-P-Edit_Points" "TSMorph.guide/I-men-P-Edit_Points"
@Prev "I-men-P-Preview"
@Toc "I-men-P"

Info Window Project/Edit Points menu item
.........................................

This is the same as the @{"Edit Points" Link "I-gad-Edit_Points"} gadget.

It opens the @{"Control Window" Link "Con"} and @{"Edit Windows" Link "Edit"} to allow editing of the
control points. If these windows are already open then the Control
Window is activated.


@EndNode

@Node "I-Key" "TSMorph.guide/I-Key"
@Prev "I-men"
@Toc "Info"

Keyboard controls in the Info Window
====================================

The following keyboard controls are available in the Info Window:

     @{b}o@{ub}  Activate @{"File One" Link "I-gad-File_One"} gadget
        With @{b}shift@{ub} - show file requester - See @{"Get File One" Link "I-gad-Get_File_One"}.
     
     @{b}t@{ub}  Activate @{"File Two" Link "I-gad-File_Two"} gadget
        With @{b}shift@{ub} - show file requester - See @{"Get File Two" Link "I-gad-Get_File_Two"}.
     
     @{b}1@{ub}  Activate @{"24 File 1" Link "I-gad-24_File_1"} gadget
        With @{b}shift@{ub} - show file requester - See @{"Get 24 File 1" Link "I-gad-Get_24_File_1"}.
     
     @{b}2@{ub}  Activate @{"24 File 2" Link "I-gad-24_File_2"} gadget
        With @{b}shift@{ub} - show file requester - See @{"Get 24 File 2" Link "I-gad-Get_24_File_2"}.
     
     @{b}rR@{ub} Cycle @{"Single image" Link "I-gad-Single"} gadget.
     
     @{b}f@{ub}  Activate @{"Frames" Link "I-gad-Frames"} gadget.
     
     @{b}a@{ub}  Activate @{"Start" Link "I-gad-Start"} gadget.
     
     @{b}n@{ub}  Activate @{"Name" Link "I-gad-Name"} gadget
        With @{b}shift@{ub} - show file requester - See @{"Get Name" Link "I-gad-Get_Name"}.
     
     @{b}p@{ub}  Same as @{"Edit Points" Link "I-gad-Edit_Points"} gadget

@{b}Help@{ub} displays context sensitive help using @{b}amigaguide@{ub} if available.


@EndNode

@Node "Con" "TSMorph.guide/Con"
@Next "Edit"
@Prev "Info"
@Toc "Main"

The Control Window
******************

The control window displays various gadgets for different for different
point editing modes. The title bar displays the current editing mode as
does the Mouse pointer. The screen title bar displays @{b}TSMorph@{ub} for
non-animated Warps/Morphs and @{b}TSMorph - Frame nnn@{ub} for animated
Warps/Morphs.


 @{" Gadgets    " Link "Con-gad"}        Gadgets displayed in the control window
 @{" Menus      " Link "CI-men"}        Menus on the Control Window
 @{" Edit Modes " Link "EModes"}        Point editing modes
 @{" Keyboard   " Link "Con-Key"}        Keyboard controls in the Control Window


@EndNode

@Node "Con-gad" "TSMorph.guide/Con-gad"
@Toc "Con"

Control and Image Window gadgets
================================

@font topaz.font 8

The Control Window appears with gadgets:

     --------------
     |@{"." Link "Con-gad-Close"}|  Mov |@{"  " Link "Con-gad-Depth"}|
     |------------|
     |@{" ONE " Link "EMode-One"} @{" TWO " Link "EMode-Two"}|
     |@{" REL " Link "EMode-Relative"} @{" ADD " Link "EMode-Add"}|
     |@{" DEL " Link "EMode-Delete"} @{" LNK " Link "EMode-Link"}|
     |@{" UNL " Link "EMode-Unlink"} @{" MOV " Link "EMode-Move"}|
     |@{"|<" Link "Con-gad-First"}@{"<-" Link "Con-gad-Previous"}@{"?" Link "Con-gad-Goto"}@{"->" Link "Con-gad-Next"}@{">|" Link "Con-gad-Last"}|
     --------------

Most are used to set the edit mode. The rest except the close and depth
gadgets are used to set the current @{"Frame Number" Link "Req-FrameNumber"}.


 @{" One   " Link "EMode-One"}                 Move points in one window
 @{" Two   " Link "EMode-Two"}                 Move points in both windows
 @{" Rel   " Link "EMode-Relative"}                 Move points relatively in both windows
 @{" Add   " Link "EMode-Add"}                 Add a new point
 @{" Del   " Link "EMode-Delete"}                 Delete an existing point
 @{" Lnk   " Link "EMode-Link"}                 Link two points
 @{" Unl   " Link "EMode-Unlink"}                 Unlink two points
 @{" Mov   " Link "EMode-Move"}                 Scroll the window

 @{" |<    " Link "Con-gad-First"}                 First Frame
 @{" <     " Link "Con-gad-Previous"}                 Previous Frame
 @{" ?     " Link "Con-gad-Goto"}                 Goto Frame
 @{" >     " Link "Con-gad-Next"}                 Next Frame
 @{" >|    " Link "Con-gad-Last"}                 Last Frame

 @{" Close " Link "Con-gad-Close"}                 Close window
 @{" Depth " Link "Con-gad-Depth"}                 Depth gadget


@EndNode

@Node "Con-gad-First" "TSMorph.guide/Con-gad-First"
@Next "Con-gad-Previous"
@Toc "Con-gad"

Control Window First Frame gadget
---------------------------------

This gadget goes to the first frame. This is the same as the @{"First" Link "CI-men-E-Frame-First"} menu
item.

This gadget is disabled if the Morph/Warp is not animated, or the first
frame is already displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "Con-gad-Previous" "TSMorph.guide/Con-gad-Previous"
@Next "Con-gad-Goto"
@Prev "Con-gad-First"
@Toc "Con-gad"

Control Window Previous Frame gadget
------------------------------------

This gadget goes to the previous frame. This is the same as the
@{"Previous" Link "CI-men-E-Frame-Previous"} menu item.

This gadget is disabled if the Morph/Warp is not animated, or the first
frame is currently displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "Con-gad-Goto" "TSMorph.guide/Con-gad-Goto"
@Next "Con-gad-Next"
@Prev "Con-gad-Previous"
@Toc "Con-gad"

Control Window Goto Frame gadget
--------------------------------

This gadget goes to a chosen frame. This is the same as the @{"Goto" Link "CI-men-E-Frame-Goto"} menu
item. It displays the @{"Frame Number" Link "Req-FrameNumber"} Requester.

This gadget is disabled if the Morph/Warp is not animated.


@EndNode

@Node "Con-gad-Next" "TSMorph.guide/Con-gad-Next"
@Next "Con-gad-Last"
@Prev "Con-gad-Goto"
@Toc "Con-gad"

Control Window Next Frame gadget
--------------------------------

This gadget goes to the next frame. This is the same as the @{"Next" Link "CI-men-E-Frame-Next"} menu
item.

This gadget is disabled if the Morph/Warp is not animated, or the last
frame is currently displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "Con-gad-Last" "TSMorph.guide/Con-gad-Last"
@Next "Con-gad-Close"
@Prev "Con-gad-Next"
@Toc "Con-gad"

Control Window Last Frame gadget
--------------------------------

This gadget goes to the last frame. This is the same as the @{"Last" Link "CI-men-E-Frame-Last"} menu
item.

This gadget is disabled if the Morph/Warp is not animated, or the last
frame is already displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "Con-gad-Close" "TSMorph.guide/Con-gad-Close"
@Next "Con-gad-Depth"
@Prev "Con-gad-Last"
@Toc "Con-gad"

Control Window Close gadget
---------------------------

This closes the @{"Control Window" Link "Con"}, and the @{"Edit Windows" Link "Edit"}.


@EndNode

@Node "Con-gad-Depth" "TSMorph.guide/Con-gad-Depth"
@Prev "Con-gad-Close"
@Toc "Con-gad"

Control Window Depth gadget
---------------------------

This is a standard depth gadget.


@EndNode

