@Node "CI-men-P-Exit_Points" "TSMorph.guide/CI-men-P-Exit_Points"
@Next "CI-men-P-Quit"
@Prev "CI-men-P-About"
@Toc "CI-men-P"

Control and Edit Window Project/Exit Points menu item
.....................................................

This is the same as closing the @{"Control Window" Link "Con-gad-Close"} or either of the
@{"Edit Windows" Link "E-gad-Close"}. It closes all of these windows.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-P-Quit" "TSMorph.guide/CI-men-P-Quit"
@Next "CI-men-P-Preview"
@Prev "CI-men-P-Exit_Points"
@Toc "CI-men-P"

Control and Edit Window Project/Quit menu item
..............................................

This quits @{b}TSMorph@{ub}.

If the current project has been changed but not saved then the
@{"Unsaved Project requester" Link "Req-Unsaved"} is displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-P-Preview" "TSMorph.guide/CI-men-P-Preview"
@Prev "CI-men-P-Quit"
@Toc "CI-men-P"

Control and Edit Windows Project/Preview... menu item
.....................................................

This menu item renders the image using the ARexx script supplied in the
@{"PREVIEW" Link "P-PREVIEW"} parameter.

If required it first displays the @{"Frame Number" Link "Req-FrameNumber"} requester.

This menu option is only available if @{b}reqtools.library@{ub} is available.

If the current project has been changed but not saved then the
@{"Unsaved Project requester" Link "Req-Unsaved"} is displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-E" "TSMorph.guide/CI-men-E"
@Next "men-Settings"
@Prev "CI-men-P"
@Toc "CI-men"

Control and Edit Window Edit menu
---------------------------------

This menu contains the following items with their associated Amiga
short-cuts in the @{"Control" Link "Con"} and @{"Edit" Link "Edit"} Windows:


 @{" Add Grid... G " Link "CI-men-E-Grid"}                     Add a grid of points
 @{" Triangulate T " Link "CI-men-E-Triangulate"}                     Convert links to triangles
 @{" Frame       » " Link "CI-men-E-Frame"}                     Change the Frame Number
 @{" Mode        » " Link "CI-men-E-EMode"}                     Set the edit mode.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-E-Grid" "TSMorph.guide/CI-men-E-Grid"
@Next "CI-men-E-Triangulate"
@Toc "CI-men-E"

Control and Edit Window Edit/Add Grid... menu item
..................................................

This menu item displays the @{"Add Grid" Link "Req-Add_Grid"} requester to add a grid of points
to the images.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-E-Triangulate" "TSMorph.guide/CI-men-E-Triangulate"
@Next "CI-men-E-Frame"
@Prev "CI-men-E-Grid"
@Toc "CI-men-E"

Control and Edit Window Edit/Triangulate menu item
..................................................

This menu item deletes all links between points and attempts to convert
them to triangles (similar to the @{"MODE=24" Link "P-MODE"} option of @{b}TSMorph-render@{ub}). If
the current project has been changed then the @{"Unsaved Project" Link "Req-Unsaved"} requester
is displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-E-Frame" "TSMorph.guide/CI-men-E-Frame"
@Next "CI-men-E-EMode"
@Prev "CI-men-E-Triangulate"
@Toc "CI-men-E"

Control and Edit Windows Frame sub menu
.......................................

This sub menu contains the following items with their associated Amiga
short-cuts in the @{"Control" Link "Con"} and @{"Edit" Link "Edit"} Windows:


 @{" First    < " Link "CI-men-E-Frame-First"}                        First Frame
 @{" Previous - " Link "CI-men-E-Frame-Previous"}                        Previous Frame
 @{" Goto...  . " Link "CI-men-E-Frame-Goto"}                        Goto Frame
 @{" Next     + " Link "CI-men-E-Frame-Next"}                        Next Frame
 @{" Last     > " Link "CI-men-E-Frame-Last"}                        Last Frame


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-E-Frame-First" "TSMorph.guide/CI-men-E-Frame-First"
@Toc "CI-men-E-Frame"

Control and Edit Windows Frame/First menu item
**********************************************

This menu item goes to the first frame. This is the same as the @{"First" Link "Con-gad-First"}
gadget.

This menu item is disabled if the Morph/Warp is not animated, or the
first frame is already displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-E-Frame-Previous" "TSMorph.guide/CI-men-E-Frame-Previous"
@Toc "CI-men-E-Frame"

Control and Edit Windows Frame/Previous menu item
*************************************************

This menu item goes to the previous frame. This is the same as the
@{"Previous" Link "Con-gad-Previous"} gadget.

This menu item is disabled if the Morph/Warp is not animated, or the
first frame is already displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-E-Frame-Goto" "TSMorph.guide/CI-men-E-Frame-Goto"
@Toc "CI-men-E-Frame"

Control and Edit Windows Frame/Goto menu item
*********************************************

This menu item goes to a chosen frame. This is the same as the @{"Goto" Link "Con-gad-Goto"}
gadget. It displays the @{"Frame Number" Link "Req-FrameNumber"} Requester.

This menu item is disabled if the Morph/Warp is not animated, or the
first frame is already displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-E-Frame-Next" "TSMorph.guide/CI-men-E-Frame-Next"
@Toc "CI-men-E-Frame"

Control and Edit Windows Frame/Next menu item
*********************************************

This menu item goes to the next frame. This is the same as the @{"Next" Link "Con-gad-Next"}
gadget.

This menu item is disabled if the Morph/Warp is not animated, or the
last frame is already displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-E-Frame-Last" "TSMorph.guide/CI-men-E-Frame-Last"
@Toc "CI-men-E-Frame"

Control and Edit Windows Frame/Last menu item
*********************************************

This menu item goes to the last frame. This is the same as the @{"Last" Link "Con-gad-Last"}
gadget.

This menu item is disabled if the Morph/Warp is not animated, or the
last frame is already displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-E-EMode" "TSMorph.guide/CI-men-E-EMode"
@Prev "CI-men-E-Frame"
@Toc "CI-men-E"

Control and Edit Window Edit/Mode sub menu
..........................................

This sub menu contains the following items with their associated Amiga
short-cuts in the @{"Control" Link "Con"} and @{"Edit" Link "Edit"} Windows:


 @{" Edit One  1 " Link "EMode-One"}               Move points in one window
 @{" Edit Two  2 " Link "EMode-Two"}               Move points in both windows
 @{" Edit Rel  3 " Link "EMode-Relative"}               Move points relatively in both windows
 @{" Add       4 " Link "EMode-Add"}               Add a new point
 @{" Delete    5 " Link "EMode-Delete"}               Delete an existing point
 @{" Link      6 " Link "EMode-Link"}               Link two points
 @{" Unlink    7 " Link "EMode-Unlink"}               Unlink two points
 @{" None      8 " Link "EMode-Move"}               Scroll the window


@EndNode

@Node "men-Settings" "TSMorph.guide/men-Settings"
@Prev "CI-men-E"
@Toc "CI-men"

Settings menu
-------------

This menu contains the following items with their associated Amiga
short-cuts in the @{"Control" Link "Con"}, @{"Info" Link "Info"} and @{"Edit" Link "Edit"} Windows. Settings can be set
using @{"Parameters" Link "Par"}. All menu items which display requesters will not be
available if @{b}reqtools.library@{ub} is not available. Items requiring
@{b}opal.library@{ub} will not be available if @{b}opal.library@{ub} is not available.


 @{" Create Icons?        " Link "P-CREATEICONS"}                Create Icons on projects?
 @{" Change Palette?    P " Link "P-CHANGEPALETTE"}                Use Image palette?
 @{" Zoom?              Z " Link "P-ZOOM"}                Zoom Image?
 @{" Open Mode          » " Link "P-OPENMODE"}                How to open images
 @{" Public Screen...     " Link "P-PUBSCREEN"}                Screen for @{b}TSMorph@{ub}
 @{" Custom Mode...       " Link "P-CUSTOMMODE"}                Mode of Custom screen to open
 @{" Custom Depth...      " Link "P-CUSTOMDEPTH"}                Depth of Custom screen to open
 @{" Preview Script...    " Link "P-PREVIEW"}                ARexx preview script

 @{" Create Prefs Icons?  " Link "P-CREATEICONSP"}                Create Icons on settings
 @{" Keep Settings?       " Link "P-KEEPSETTINGS"}                Keep settings on Quit
 @{" Load Settings...     " Link "men-S-LoadS"}                Display file requester to load settings
 @{" Save Settings        " Link "men-S-SaveS"}                Save settings in ENVARC:TSMorph/TSMorph.prefs
 @{" Save Settings As...  " Link "men-S-SaveSAs"}                Display file requester to save settings

 @{" Create Render Icons? " Link "P-CREATEICONSR"}                Create Icons on images?
 @{" DX...                " Link "P-DX"}                Horizontal skip
 @{" DY...                " Link "P-DY"}                Vertical skip
 @{" Load Script...       " Link "P-LOADSCRIPT"}                ARexx load script
 @{" Pre Script...        " Link "P-PRESCRIPT"}                ARexx pre frame script
 @{" Post Script...       " Link "P-POSTSCRIPT"}                ARexx post frame script
 @{" Depth                " Link "P-DEPTH"}                Morphing algorithm depth
 @{" Mode               » " Link "P-MODE"}                Morphing algorithm mode
 @{" Save Format        » " Link "P-SAVEFORMAT"}                Image save format
 @{" JPEG Quality         " Link "P-QUALITY"}                Quality of JPEG images
 @{" Render Screen...     " Link "P-PUBSCREENR"}                Public screen for @{b}TSMorph-render@{ub}
 @{" Anti-Alias?          " Link "P-ANTIALIAS"}                Anti-Alias the output images
 @{" Integer?             " Link "P-INTEGER"}                Use integer maths

 @{" Reset To Defaults    " Link "men-S-ResetD"}                Reset to default settings
 @{" Last Saved           " Link "men-S-LastS"}                Restore from ENVARC:TSMorph/TSMorph.prefs
 @{" Restore              " Link "men-S-Restore"}                Restore from ENV:TSMorph/TSMorph.prefs

 @{" Continuous Help?     " Link "P-HELP"}                Display continuous help


@EndNode

@Node "men-S-LoadS" "TSMorph.guide/men-S-LoadS"
@Toc "men-Settings"

Setting/Load Settings... menu item
..................................

This displays an ASL requester to load @{"settings" Link "Par"} into the currently
running program.

The default name is @{b}TSMorph.prefs@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "men-S-SaveS" "TSMorph.guide/men-S-SaveS"
@Toc "men-Settings"

Settings/Save Settings menu item
................................

This saves the current @{"settings" Link "Par"} in @{b}ENVARC:TSMorph/TSMorph.prefs@{ub} and
@{b}ENV:TSMorph/TSMorph.prefs@{ub}.

If @{"CREATEICONSP" Link "P-CREATEICONSP"} is set then an Icon is saved as well

Unless @{"KEEPSETTINGS" Link "P-KEEPSETTINGS"} is set to NO current settings are saved in
@{b}ENV:TSMorph/TSMorph.prefs@{ub} whenever @{b}TSMorph@{ub} is quit.


@EndNode

@Node "men-S-SaveSAs" "TSMorph.guide/men-S-SaveSAs"
@Toc "men-Settings"

Setting/Save Settings As... menu item
.....................................

This displays an ASL requester to save the current @{"settings" Link "Par"}.

If @{"CREATEICONSP" Link "P-CREATEICONSP"} is set then an Icon is saved as well

The default name is @{b}TSMorph.prefs@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "men-S-ResetD" "TSMorph.guide/men-S-ResetD"
@Toc "men-Settings"

Setting/Reset To Defaults menu item
...................................

This resets @{"settings" Link "Par"} to there default values.

If some @{"Image windows" Link "Edit"} are open and @{"CHANGEPALETTE" Link "P-CHANGEPALETTE"} is set to @{b}OFF@{ub} then it
will stay @{b}OFF@{ub}. The same applies to @{"ZOOM" Link "P-ZOOM"}.


@EndNode

@Node "men-S-LastS" "TSMorph.guide/men-S-LastS"
@Toc "men-Settings"

Settings/Last Saved menu item
.............................

This reset @{"settings" Link "Par"} to the values last saved in
@{b}ENVARC:TSMorph/TSMorph.prefs@{ub} (overridden by any @{b}Tool Types@{ub}).

If some @{"Image windows" Link "Edit"} are open and @{"CHANGEPALETTE" Link "P-CHANGEPALETTE"} is set to @{b}OFF@{ub} then it
will stay @{b}OFF@{ub}. The same applies to @{"ZOOM" Link "P-ZOOM"}.


@EndNode

@Node "men-S-Restore" "TSMorph.guide/men-S-Restore"
@Toc "men-Settings"

Setting/Restore menu item
.........................

This resets @{"settings" Link "Par"} to the values last saved in
@{b}ENV:TSMorph/TSMorph.prefs@{ub} (overridden by any @{b}Tool Types@{ub}). Settings are
saved in this file whenever @{b}TSMorph@{ub} is quit if @{"KEEPSETTINGS" Link "P-KEEPSETTINGS"} is set to
@{b}YES@{ub}.

If some @{"Image windows" Link "Edit"} are open and @{"CHANGEPALETTE" Link "P-CHANGEPALETTE"} is set to @{b}OFF@{ub} then it
will stay @{b}OFF@{ub}. The same applies to @{"ZOOM" Link "P-ZOOM"}.


@EndNode

@Node "Con-Key" "TSMorph.guide/Con-Key"
@Toc "Con"

Keyboard controls in the Control Window
=======================================

@{b}Help@{ub} displays context sensitive help using @{b}amigaguide@{ub} if available.


@EndNode

@Node "Edit" "TSMorph.guide/Edit"
@Next "EModes"
@Prev "Con"
@Toc "Main"

The Edit Windows
****************

The Edit windows display Workbench displayable versions of the images
to be morphed along with the control points. The window title displays
the file name, the screen title displays the full file name. The mouse
pointer shows the current editing mode. The windows are sizeable and
have scrollbars. The menus displayed are the same as the @{"Control Window" Link "Con"}.

The first click in these windows is ignored.

If @{"EGS" Link "P-EGS"} is being used then the windows are displayed on the @{b}EGS@{ub} screen
without menus. Keyboard short cuts @{b}1-8@{ub} are still available. The windows
do not, however, automatically scroll.


 @{" Gadgets  " Link "E-gad"}       Gadgets on the Edit Windows
 @{" Menus    " Link "CI-men"}       Menus on the Edit Windows
 @{" Keyboard " Link "E-Key"}       Keyboard controls on the Edit Windows
 @{" Modes    " Link "EModes"}       Point editing modes.


@EndNode

@Node "E-gad" "TSMorph.guide/E-gad"
@Toc "Edit"

Gadgets on the Edit Windows
===========================

@font topaz.font 8

The Edit Windows appears with gadgets:

     ------------------
     |@{"." Link "E-gad-Close"}|filename  |@{" " Link "E-gad-Zoom"}@{" " Link "E-gad-Depth"}|
     |----------------|
     |             |  |
     |             |@{"||" Link "E-gad-Vert"}|
     |             |@{"||" Link "E-gad-Vert"}|
     |             |@{"||" Link "E-gad-Vert"}|
     |             |@{"||" Link "E-gad-Vert"}|
     |             |@{"/|" Link "E-gad-Up"}|
     |             |@{"\|" Link "E-gad-Down"}|
     |----------------|
     |@{"-------" Link "E-gad-Horiz"}@{"<-" Link "E-gad-Left"}@{"->" Link "E-gad-Right"}|@{"//" Link "E-gad-Size"}|
     ------------------


 @{" Horizontal scroll gadget " Link "E-gad-Horiz"}            Scrolls image horizontally
 @{" Vertical scroll gadget   " Link "E-gad-Vert"}            Scrolls image vertically
 @{" Up gadget                " Link "E-gad-Up"}            Scroll image up
 @{" Down gadget              " Link "E-gad-Down"}            Scroll image down
 @{" Left gadget              " Link "E-gad-Left"}            Scroll image left
 @{" Right gadget             " Link "E-gad-Right"}            Scroll image right

 @{" Close gadget             " Link "E-gad-Close"}            Close Edit and Control Windows
 @{" Zoom gadget              " Link "E-gad-Zoom"}            Zoom window
 @{" Depth gadget             " Link "E-gad-Depth"}            Depth gadget
 @{" Sizing gadget            " Link "E-gad-Size"}            Sizing gadget


@EndNode

@Node "E-gad-Horiz" "TSMorph.guide/E-gad-Horiz"
@Next "E-gad-Vert"
@Toc "E-gad"

Edit Windows Horizontal gadget
------------------------------

This gadget can be used to scroll the image horizontally.


@EndNode

@Node "E-gad-Vert" "TSMorph.guide/E-gad-Vert"
@Next "E-gad-Up"
@Prev "E-gad-Horiz"
@Toc "E-gad"

Edit Windows Vertical gadget
----------------------------

This gadget can be used to scroll the image vertically.


@EndNode

@Node "E-gad-Up" "TSMorph.guide/E-gad-Up"
@Next "E-gad-Down"
@Prev "E-gad-Vert"
@Toc "E-gad"

Edit Windows Up gadget
----------------------

This gadget can be used to scroll the image up.

Holding down @{b}shift@{ub} will cause the window to scroll one pixel at a time.


@EndNode

@Node "E-gad-Down" "TSMorph.guide/E-gad-Down"
@Next "E-gad-Left"
@Prev "E-gad-Up"
@Toc "E-gad"

Edit Windows Down gadget
------------------------

This gadget can be used to scroll the image down.

Holding down @{b}shift@{ub} will cause the window to scroll one pixel at a time.


@EndNode

@Node "E-gad-Left" "TSMorph.guide/E-gad-Left"
@Next "E-gad-Right"
@Prev "E-gad-Down"
@Toc "E-gad"

Edit Windows Left gadget
------------------------

This gadget can be used to scroll the image left.

Holding down @{b}shift@{ub} will cause the window to scroll one pixel at a time.


@EndNode

@Node "E-gad-Right" "TSMorph.guide/E-gad-Right"
@Next "E-gad-Close"
@Prev "E-gad-Left"
@Toc "E-gad"

Edit Windows Right gadget
-------------------------

This gadget can be used to scroll the image right.

Holding down @{b}shift@{ub} will cause the window to scroll one pixel at a time.


@EndNode

@Node "E-gad-Close" "TSMorph.guide/E-gad-Close"
@Next "E-gad-Zoom"
@Prev "E-gad-Right"
@Toc "E-gad"

Edit Windows Close gadget
-------------------------

This closes the @{"Control Window" Link "Con"}, and the @{"Edit Windows" Link "Edit"}.


@EndNode

@Node "E-gad-Zoom" "TSMorph.guide/E-gad-Zoom"
@Next "E-gad-Depth"
@Prev "E-gad-Close"
@Toc "E-gad"

Edit Windows Zoom gadget
------------------------

This is a standard Zoom gadget. It swaps the size between maximum and
minimum

Maximum is the smaller of the size of the image or the size of the
screen.

Minimum is the minimum required for all gadgets to still be visible.


@EndNode

@Node "E-gad-Depth" "TSMorph.guide/E-gad-Depth"
@Next "E-gad-Size"
@Prev "E-gad-Zoom"
@Toc "E-gad"

Edit Windows Depth gadget
-------------------------

This is a standard depth gadget.


@EndNode

@Node "E-gad-Size" "TSMorph.guide/E-gad-Size"
@Prev "E-gad-Depth"
@Toc "E-gad"

Edit Windows Sizing gadget
--------------------------

This a standard sizing gadget. See @{"Zoom" Link "E-gad-Zoom"} gadget for the sizing limits


@EndNode

@Node "E-Key" "TSMorph.guide/E-Key"
@Toc "Edit"

Keyboard controls in the Edit Windows
=====================================

The number keys can be used to set the @{"Edit Mode" Link "EModes"}.


 @{" 1 " Link "EMode-One"}               Move points in one window
 @{" 2 " Link "EMode-Two"}               Move points in both windows
 @{" 3 " Link "EMode-Relative"}               Move points relatively in both windows
 @{" 4 " Link "EMode-Add"}               Add a new point
 @{" 5 " Link "EMode-Delete"}               Delete an existing point
 @{" 6 " Link "EMode-Link"}               Link two points
 @{" 7 " Link "EMode-Unlink"}               Unlink two points
 @{" 8 " Link "EMode-Move"}               Scroll the window

@{b}Help@{ub} displays context sensitive help using @{b}amigaguide@{ub} if available.


@EndNode

@Node "EModes" "TSMorph.guide/EModes"
@Next "Req"
@Prev "Edit"
@Toc "Main"

Point editing modes
*******************

The following edit modes are available to edit points:


 @{" One      " Link "EMode-One"}               Move points in one window
 @{" Two      " Link "EMode-Two"}               Move points in both windows
 @{" Relative " Link "EMode-Relative"}               Move points relatively in both windows
 @{" Add      " Link "EMode-Add"}               Add a new point
 @{" Delete   " Link "EMode-Delete"}               Delete an existing point
 @{" Link     " Link "EMode-Link"}               Link two points
 @{" Unlink   " Link "EMode-Unlink"}               Unlink two points
 @{" Move     " Link "EMode-Move"}               Scroll the window

@{b}Note:@{ub} The @{b}menu button@{ub} can always be used to abort the current operation
before releasing the select button.

Modes can be set using gadgets in the @{"Control Window" Link "Con-gad"} or by using @{"menus" Link "CI-men-E-EMode"}
on the @{"Control" Link "Con"} and @{"Edit" Link "Edit"} Windows.


@EndNode

@Node "EMode-One" "TSMorph.guide/EMode-One"
@Next "EMode-Two"
@Toc "EModes"

Edit Mode One
=============

This mode is used to move a point in one of the @{"Edit Windows" Link "Edit"}.

The @{"Control Windows" Link "Con"} title is set to @{i}One@{ui}.

The Mouse Pointer is set to @{b}ONE@{ub}.

Points can be clicked and moved in either of the windows with the mouse
- the point will only move in the selected window.


@EndNode

@Node "EMode-Two" "TSMorph.guide/EMode-Two"
@Next "EMode-Relative"
@Prev "EMode-One"
@Toc "EModes"

Edit Mode Two
=============

This mode is used to move a point in both of the @{"Edit Windows" Link "Edit"}.

The @{"Control Windows" Link "Con"} title is set to @{i}Two@{ui}.

The Mouse Pointer is set to @{b}TWO@{ub}.

Points can be clicked and moved in both of the windows with the mouse -
the point will move in both windows to the same absolute position.


@EndNode

@Node "EMode-Relative" "TSMorph.guide/EMode-Relative"
@Next "EMode-Add"
@Prev "EMode-Two"
@Toc "EModes"

Edit Mode Relative
==================

This mode is used to move a point in both of the @{"Edit Windows" Link "Edit"}.

The @{"Control Windows" Link "Con"} title is set to @{i}Rel@{ui}.

The Mouse Pointer is set to @{b}REL@{ub}.

Points can be clicked and moved in both of the windows with the mouse -
the point will move in both windows to the same relative position.


@EndNode

@Node "EMode-Add" "TSMorph.guide/EMode-Add"
@Next "EMode-Delete"
@Prev "EMode-Relative"
@Toc "EModes"

Edit Mode Add
=============

This mode is used to add a point in both of the @{"Edit Windows" Link "Edit"}.

The @{"Control Windows" Link "Con"} title is set to @{i}Add@{ui}.

The Mouse Pointer is set to @{b}ADD@{ub}.

Points can be added in either of the windows by clicking the mouse - the
point will added to both windows to the same absolute position.


@EndNode

@Node "EMode-Delete" "TSMorph.guide/EMode-Delete"
@Next "EMode-Link"
@Prev "EMode-Add"
@Toc "EModes"

Edit Mode Delete
================

This mode is used to delete a point in both of the @{"Edit Windows" Link "Edit"}.

The @{"Control Windows" Link "Con"} title is set to @{i}Del@{ui}.

The Mouse Pointer is set to @{b}DEL@{ub}.

Points can be deleted in either of the windows by clicking the mouse -
the point will deleted from both windows. Any @{"links" Link "EMode-Link"} will also be
removed.


@EndNode

@Node "EMode-Link" "TSMorph.guide/EMode-Link"
@Next "EMode-Unlink"
@Prev "EMode-Delete"
@Toc "EModes"

Edit Mode Link
==============

This mode is used to link two points in both of the @{"Edit Windows" Link "Edit"}.

The @{"Control Windows" Link "Con"} title is initially set to @{i}L1@{ui}.

The Mouse Pointer is set to @{b}L1@{ub}.

A point can then be selected in either of the windows by clicking the
mouse.

The @{"Control Windows" Link "Con"} title is then set to @{i}L2@{ui}.

The Mouse Pointer is set to @{b}L2@{ub}.

Another point can then be selected in either of the windows by clicking
the mouse. The points will be joined by a line.

@{b}Note:@{ub} this line is to enable points to be identified more easily. It is
not used by the rendering process.


@EndNode

@Node "EMode-Unlink" "TSMorph.guide/EMode-Unlink"
@Next "EMode-Move"
@Prev "EMode-Link"
@Toc "EModes"

Edit Mode Unlink
================

This mode is used to unlink two linked points in both of the
@{"Edit Windows" Link "Edit"}.

The @{"Control Windows" Link "Con"} title is initially set to @{i}U1@{ui}.

The Mouse Pointer is set to @{b}U1@{ub}.

A point can then be selected in either of the windows by clicking the
mouse.

The @{"Control Windows" Link "Con"} title is then set to @{i}U2@{ui}.

The Mouse Pointer is set to @{b}U2@{ub}.

Another point can then be selected in either of the windows by clicking
the mouse. If the points are currently joined then the line will be
removed.


@EndNode

@Node "EMode-Move" "TSMorph.guide/EMode-Move"
@Prev "EMode-Unlink"
@Toc "EModes"

Edit Mode Move
==============

In this mode no points are edited.

The @{"Control Windows" Link "Con"} title is set to @{i}Mov@{ui}.

The Mouse Pointer is set to @{b}Mov@{ub}.

Clicking in the window and moving the mouse will scroll the window.

This is the initial mode when the @{"Edit Windows" Link "Edit"} are opened.

If @{"EGS" Link "P-EGS"} is being used then the windows will not scroll.


@EndNode

@Node "Req" "TSMorph.guide/Req"
@Next "Interface"
@Prev "EModes"
@Toc "Main"

Requesters which appear
***********************

The following requesters are produced:


 @{" Unsaved Project " Link "Req-Unsaved"}                Quitting having not saved
 @{" About requester " Link "Req-About"}                Version Information
 @{" Error requester " Link "Req-Error"}                Error messages
 @{" Add Grid        " Link "Req-Add_Grid"}                Add a grid of points
 @{" Frame Number?   " Link "Req-FrameNumber"}                Choose a Frame Number

 @{" Progress        " Link "Req-Progress"}                Progress
 @{" Really quit?    " Link "Req-Really_quit"}                Really quit?


@EndNode

@Node "Req-Unsaved" "TSMorph.guide/Req-Unsaved"
@Next "Req-About"
@Toc "Req"

Unsaved project requester
=========================

This requester is displayed when attempting to quit, preview render or
triangulate without having saved a project.

It displays 3 or 4 options (depending on if @{b}amigaguide@{ub} is available):

     @{b}Save:@{ub}    Save the project and quit, render or triangulate
     @{b}Help:@{ub}    Display help (only shown if available)
     @{b}Abandon:@{ub} Quit, preview or triangulate without saving the project
     @{b}Cancel:@{ub}  Do not save and do not quit, preview or triangulate

If @{b}reqtools.library(38)@{ub} is available then this will be used and
keyboard short-cuts (the first character of the option) will be
available and underlined.


@EndNode

@Node "Req-About" "TSMorph.guide/Req-About"
@Next "Req-Error"
@Prev "Req-Unsaved"
@Toc "Req"

About requester
===============

This requester is displayed when @{b}About...@{ub} is chosen on a menu on the
@{"Info Window" Link "I-men-P-About"} or @{"Control or Edit Windows" Link "CI-men-P-About"}. It displays version information.

If @{b}reqtools.library(38)@{ub} is available then this will be used and
keyboard short-cuts (the first character of the option) will be
available and underlined.


@EndNode

@Node "Req-Error" "TSMorph.guide/Req-Error"
@Next "Req-Add_Grid"
@Prev "Req-About"
@Toc "Req"

Error requesters
================

This requester is displayed if an error occurs. It displays an error
message and gives one (or two) options.

If @{b}amigaguide@{ub} is available then the first option will be @{b}Help@{ub} - this
will display detailed information on the error message.

The last option is @{b}Quit@{ub} for fatal errors, and @{b}OK@{ub} for non fatal errors.

See @{"Errors" Link "Errors"} for details on error messages.

If @{b}reqtools.library(38)@{ub} is available then this will be used and
keyboard short-cuts (the first character of the option) will be
available and underlined.

If @{"EGS" Link "P-EGS"} is being used and the @{"edit" Link "Edit"} windows are open then the requester
will appear on the @{b}EGS@{ub} screen.


@EndNode

@Node "Req-Add_Grid" "TSMorph.guide/Req-Add_Grid"
@Next "Req-FrameNumber"
@Prev "Req-Error"
@Toc "Req"

Add Grid requester
==================

@font topaz.font 8

The Add Grid requester appears as below when the @{"Add Grid..." Link "CI-men-E-Grid"} menu item
is chosen

     ---------------
     |@{"." Link "Req-Add_Grid-gad-Close"}|Add Grid|@{" " Link "Req-Add_Grid-gad-Depth"}|
     |-------------|
     | @{u}X@{uu} Cells @{"..." Link "Req-Add_Grid-gad-X_Cells"}|
     | @{u}Y@{uu} Cells @{"..." Link "Req-Add_Grid-gad-Y_Cells"}|
     |             |
     | @{" OK " Link "Req-Add_Grid-gad-OK"} @{"Cancel" Link "Req-Add_Grid-gad-Cancel"}|
     ---------------

The following gadgets are displayed in the requester with their
associated keyboard equivalents:


 @{" X Cells   X " Link "Req-Add_Grid-gad-X_Cells"}                         Set number of X cells
 @{" Y Cells   Y " Link "Req-Add_Grid-gad-Y_Cells"}                         Set number of Y Cells
 @{" OK        O " Link "Req-Add_Grid-gad-OK"}                         Add points
 @{" Cancel    C " Link "Req-Add_Grid-gad-Cancel"}                         Cancel requester
 @{" Close       " Link "Req-Add_Grid-gad-Close"}                         Close gadget
 @{" Depth       " Link "Req-Add_Grid-gad-Depth"}                         Depth gadget


@EndNode

@Node "Req-Add_Grid-gad-X_Cells" "TSMorph.guide/Req-Add_Grid-gad-X_Cells"
@Next "Req-Add_Grid-gad-Y_Cells"
@Toc "Req-Add_Grid"

Add Grid X Cells gadget
-----------------------

This gadget is used to input the number of horizontal cells of points
to add. The minimum number is @{b}1@{ub}. The default value displayed is @{b}5@{ub}.

This gadget can be activated by using the @{b}X@{ub} key.


@EndNode

@Node "Req-Add_Grid-gad-Y_Cells" "TSMorph.guide/Req-Add_Grid-gad-Y_Cells"
@Next "Req-Add_Grid-gad-OK"
@Prev "Req-Add_Grid-gad-X_Cells"
@Toc "Req-Add_Grid"

Add Grid Y Cells gadget
-----------------------

This gadget is used to input the number of vertical cells of points to
add. The minimum number is @{b}1@{ub}. The default value displayed is @{b}5@{ub}.

This gadget can be activated by using the @{b}Y@{ub} key.


@EndNode

@Node "Req-Add_Grid-gad-OK" "TSMorph.guide/Req-Add_Grid-gad-OK"
@Next "Req-Add_Grid-gad-Cancel"
@Prev "Req-Add_Grid-gad-Y_Cells"
@Toc "Req-Add_Grid"

Add Grid OK gadget
------------------

Selecting this gadget adds points of cells to the images. The number of
horizontal cells can be set in the @{"X Cells" Link "Req-Add_Grid-gad-X_Cells"} gadget and the number of
vertical cells in the @{"Y Cells" Link "Req-Add_Grid-gad-Y_Cells"} gadget.

The @{b}O@{ub} key is the same as using this gadget.


@EndNode

@Node "Req-Add_Grid-gad-Cancel" "TSMorph.guide/Req-Add_Grid-gad-Cancel"
@Next "Req-Add_Grid-gad-Close"
@Prev "Req-Add_Grid-gad-OK"
@Toc "Req-Add_Grid"

Add Grid Cancel gadget
----------------------

This gadget cancels the Add Grid requester without adding any points.

The @{b}C@{ub} key is the same as using this gadget.


@EndNode

@Node "Req-Add_Grid-gad-Close" "TSMorph.guide/Req-Add_Grid-gad-Close"
@Next "Req-Add_Grid-gad-Depth"
@Prev "Req-Add_Grid-gad-Cancel"
@Toc "Req-Add_Grid"

Add Grid Close gadget
---------------------

This is the same as the @{"Cancel" Link "Req-Add_Grid-gad-Cancel"} gadget and cancels the requester.


@EndNode

@Node "Req-Add_Grid-gad-Depth" "TSMorph.guide/Req-Add_Grid-gad-Depth"
@Prev "Req-Add_Grid-gad-Close"
@Toc "Req-Add_Grid"

Add Grid Depth gadget
---------------------

This is a standard depth gadget.


@EndNode

@Node "Req-FrameNumber" "TSMorph.guide/Req-FrameNumber"
@Next "Req-Progress"
@Prev "Req-Add_Grid"
@Toc "Req"

Choose a Frame Number requester
===============================

This requester is displayed when the @{"Edit Points" Link "I-gad-Edit_Points"} gadget is selected
(and there is more than one frame) on an animated Morph/Warp, or the
@{"Goto" Link "Con-gad-Goto"} gadget or @{"Goto" Link "CI-men-E-Frame-Goto"} menu item is selected, or the @{"Preview..." Link "CI-men-P-Preview"} or
@{"Preview..." Link "I-men-P-Preview"} menu item is selected.

It displays the first and last frame number and allows input of the
required frame number.

It displays @{b}OK@{ub}, @{b}Help@{ub} (if @{b}amigaguide@{ub} is available) and @{b}Cancel@{ub} gadgets.
The keyboard shortcuts (@{b}O@{ub},@{b}H@{ub} and @{b}C@{ub}) are underlined.


@EndNode

@Node "Req-Progress" "TSMorph.guide/Req-Progress"
@Next "Req-Really_quit"
@Prev "Req-FrameNumber"
@Toc "Req"

Progress requester
==================

This requester is displayed by @{b}TSMorph-render@{ub}. It shows a list view of
information messages, and the current frame and line being calculated.

It also displays a @{b}stop@{ub} button and a zoom and depth gadget.

The @{b}stop@{ub} gadget is checked every line. Clicking it displays the
@{"Really quit?" Link "Req-Really_quit"} requester allowing the program to be stopped.

The @{b}Help@{ub} key displays help.


@EndNode

@Node "Req-Really_quit" "TSMorph.guide/Req-Really_quit"
@Prev "Req-Progress"
@Toc "Req"

Really quit? requester
======================

This requester is displayed when the @{b}stop@{ub} gadget is clicked on the
@{"Progress" Link "Req-Progress"} requester.  It displays two (or three) options @{b}Quit@{ub} (@{b}Help@{ub}) and
@{b}Continue@{ub}.  @{b}Quit@{ub} quits the program, @{b}Continue@{ub} restarts the calculation,
@{b}Help@{ub} is displayed if @{b}amigaguide@{ub} is available and displays help.

If @{b}reqtools.library(38)@{ub} is available then this will be used and
keyboard short-cuts (the first character of the option) will be
available and underlined.


@EndNode

@Node "Interface" "TSMorph.guide/Interface"
@Next "File_Format"
@Prev "Req"
@Toc "Main"

Changing the Interface
**********************

All the gadgets in the @{"Control" Link "Con-gad"} window, and the mouse pointers can be
edited.

The brushes are stored in the directory @{b}Brush/@{ub}. All may be edited and
using e.g. DPaint.

The following brushes are size @{b}38x34@{ub}:

     add
     del
     link
     none
     one
     rel
     two
     unlink

The following are @{b}15x15@{ub}:

     1st
     Last
     Next
     Prev

The following is @{b}16x15@{ub}:

     Goto

The mouse pointers are stored in the directory @{b}Cursor/@{ub}. All may be
edited using the Workbench Pointer editor.

The following Pointers can be edited:

     Xadd
     Xdel
     Xl1
     Xl2
     Xmov
     Xone
     Xrel
     Xtwo
     Xu1
     Xu2


@EndNode

@Node "File_Format" "TSMorph.guide/File_Format"
@Next "AR"
@Prev "Interface"
@Toc "Main"

Internal file formats
*********************

The file format is subject to change at any time.

The current format for the main file is:

     TSMorph 1.2
     file_name_one
     file_name_two
     24_bit_file_name_1
     24_bit_file_name_2
     anim_file_name
     w=a,h=b,Frames=c,Single=d,Start=e
     x=n,y=m,x1=o,y1=p
     .
     .
     .
     p1=i,p2=j
     .
     .
     .

where @{b}TSMorph 1.2@{ub} is a header record (not present in the previous
version of @{b}TSMorph@{ub}, old formats can still be loaded producing a
@{"warning message" Link "Err-OldFormat"}), a is the width, b the height, c the number of frames,
d is 0 for Morph, 1 for Warp, 2 for Anim Morph and 3 for Anim Warp, e
is the start frame number, n,m are coordinates on the first image, o,p
on the second image, and i and j are the number of the points to join
(starting from 0).

For animated Warps and Morphs the main file contains no points. Each
frame has a set of points held in a file named with .nnn after the main
file name, where nnn is the frame number. This file has a header of
@{b}TSMorph 2.0@{ub} and then has the Points details.


@EndNode

@Node "AR" "TSMorph.guide/AR"
@Next "Algorithms"
@Prev "File_Format"
@Toc "Main"

ARexx interface to TSMorph-render and TSMorph
*********************************************

ARexx scripts are run before and after each image is rendered, and
before each 24 bit image is loaded. The script names can be supplied as
parameters (@{"LOADSCRIPT" Link "P-LOADSCRIPT"}, @{"PRESCRIPT" Link "P-PRESCRIPT"} and @{"POSTSCRIPT" Link "P-POSTSCRIPT"}) to @{b}TSMorph-render@{ub}.

An ARexx script can also be run by @{b}TSMorph@{ub} to preview render an image.
The script name is supplied in the @{"PREVIEW" Link "P-PREVIEW"} parameter.

The suffix to each ARexx script should be @{b}.TSM@{ub}.


 @{" Loadscript " Link "AR-Loadscript"}              Run before loading 24 bit image
 @{" Prescript  " Link "AR-Prescript"}              Run before rendering
 @{" Postscript " Link "AR-Postscript"}              Run after rendering

 @{" Preview    " Link "AR-Preview"}              Preview render an image


@EndNode

@Node "AR-Loadscript" "TSMorph.guide/AR-Loadscript"
@Next "AR-Prescript"
@Toc "AR"

ARexx script run before loading 24 bit image
============================================

This script is run before each 24 bit ILBM image is loaded.

It is passed the following parameters:

     @{b}Frame@{ub}       : The current frame number, starting at @{"Start" Link "I-gad-Start"}.
     @{b}TotalFrames@{ub} : The total number of frames being rendered.
     @{b}Single@{ub}      : Set to 1 if a Warp, 0 for a Morph, 2 for Anim Morph, 3 for Anim Warp.
     @{b}Image@{ub}       : Set to 0 for 1st image, 1 for second.
     @{b}FileName@{ub}    : Name of file just rendered.

This script can be used to change the format of the input file (by
running it through a conversion program).

One example is included:
     @{"Loadscript.TSM" ALINK "Rexx/Loadscript.TSM/Main"} - Do nothing example


@EndNode

@Node "AR-Prescript" "TSMorph.guide/AR-Prescript"
@Next "AR-Postscript"
@Prev "AR-Loadscript"
@Toc "AR"

ARexx script run before rendering
=================================

This script is run before each image is rendered.

It is also called for the first image (for warps and morphs) and for
the last image (for morphs). By default the first and last frames are
not rendered. @{b}Produce@{ub} will need to be set to 1 to output these frames.
This allows the first and last frames to be converted to the same
format as the other output images.

It is passed one parameter - @{b}Base@{ub} - the address of a structure which
contains the following:

     @{b}Frame@{ub}       = 0  : The current frame number, starting at 1 (0 for 1st frame) - read only.
     @{b}TotalFrames@{ub} = 1  : The total number of frames being rendered - read only.
     @{b}Single@{ub}      = 2  : Set to 1 if a Warp, 0 = Morph, 2 = Anim Morph, 3 = Anim Warp - read only.
     @{b}Movement@{ub}    = 3  : 0 to 1024 - the proportion of movement from first to second image.
     @{b}Red1@{ub}        = 4  : 0 to 1024 - the proportion of Image 1 Red to use.
     @{b}Green1@{ub}      = 5  : As Red1 for Green.
     @{b}Blue1@{ub}       = 6  : As Red1 for Blue.
     @{b}Red2@{ub}        = 7  : 0 to 1024 - the proportion of Image 2 Red to use.
     @{b}Green2@{ub}      = 8  : As Red2 for Green.
     @{b}Blue2@{ub}       = 9  : As Red2 for Blue.
     @{b}Produce@{ub}     = 10 : Set to 0 to not render this frame, 1 otherwise.
     @{b}RPlus@{ub}       = 11 : 0 to 255 to add to Red in rendered image.
     @{b}GPlus@{ub}       = 12 : As RPlus for Green.
     @{b}BPlus@{ub}       = 13 : As RPlus for Blue.
     @{b}RMinus@{ub}      = 14 : 0 to 255 to subtract from Red in rendered image.
     @{b}GMinus@{ub}      = 15 : As RMinus for Green.
     @{b}BMinus@{ub}      = 16 : As RMinus for Blue.
     @{b}DX@{ub}          = 17 : 0 to ? - X amount to skip - See @{"parameters" Link "Par-TSMorph-render"}.
     @{b}DY@{ub}          = 18 : 0 to ? - Y amount to skip - See @{"parameters" Link "Par-TSMorph-render"}.
     @{b}Start@{ub}       = 19 : Starting frame number.

The values of these parameters may be set and read using the @{b}GetValue@{ub}
and @{b}StoreValue@{ub} functions:

     /* To read the value of e.g. Movement use:
        integer_variable = GetValue(Base,Movement)
     */
     
     /* To set the value of e.g. Produce to 0 use:
        call StoreValue(Base,Produce,0)
     */
     
     GetValue:Procedure
        Parse arg XBase, XAdd
        return C2D(IMPORT(D2C(STRIP(XBase) + (STRIP(Xadd) * 4),4),4))
     
     StoreValue:Procedure
        Parse arg XBase, XAdd, XVal
        call EXPORT(D2C(STRIP(XBase) + (STRIP(Xadd) * 4),4),D2C(XVal,4),4)
        return

The default values passed to the script for modification are:

     @{b}Movement@{ub}            : (1024 * Frame)/(TotalFrames + 1) Morphs
                           (1024 * Frame)/TotalFrames       Warps
     
     @{b}Red1,Green1,Blue1@{ub}   : Movement                         Morphs
                           1024                             Warps
     
     @{b}Red2,Green2,Blue2@{ub}   : (1024 - Movement)                Morphs
                           0                 Irrelevant for Warps
     
     @{b}Produce@{ub}             : 1                                Rendered frames
                           0                 Frames 0 and TotalFrames+1
     @{b}RPlus,GPlus,BPlus@{ub}   : 0
     @{b}RMinus,GMinus,BMinus@{ub}: 0
     @{b}DX,DY@{ub}               : Initially set by @{"DX" Link "P-DX"} and @{"DY" Link "P-DY"} parameters

Changing these values allows acceleration of movement, colour fades
etc. and the generation of only some images (to check a long animation).

Example scripts included are:
     @{"FadeToBlack.TSM" ALINK "Rexx/FadeToBlack.TSM/Main"} - Warp fade to black
     @{"FadeToWhite.TSM" ALINK "Rexx/FadeToWhite.TSM/Main"} - Warp fade to white
     @{"PixelMorph.TSM" ALINK "Rexx/PixelMorph.TSM/Main"}  - Morph by pixelating
     @{"PixelWarp.TSM" ALINK "Rexx/PixelWarp.TSM/Main"}   - Warp pixelating
     @{"PreAll.TSM" ALINK "Rexx/PreAll.TSM/Main"}      - Render all images
     @{"Prescript.TSM" ALINK "Rexx/Prescript.TSM/Main"}   - Do nothing example


@EndNode

@Node "AR-Postscript" "TSMorph.guide/AR-Postscript"
@Next "AR-Preview"
@Prev "AR-Prescript"
@Toc "AR"

ARexx script run after rendering
================================

This script is run after each image is rendered.

It is passed the following parameters:

     @{b}Frame@{ub}       : The current frame number, starting at @{"Start" Link "I-gad-Start"}.
     @{b}TotalFrames@{ub} : The total number of frames being rendered.
     @{b}Single@{ub}      : Set to 1 if a Warp, 0 for a Morph.
     @{b}FileName@{ub}    : Name of file just rendered.

This script can be used to change the format of the output file (by
running it through a conversion program) or build an animation.

Three examples are included:
     @{"PostAnim.TSM" ALINK "Rexx/PostAnim.TSM/Main"}   - Convert to Anim
     @{"Postscript.TSM" ALINK "Rexx/Postscript.TSM/Main"} - Do nothing example
     @{"ToHam.TSM" ALINK "Rexx/ToHam.TSM/Main"}      - Convert using PPM and Wasp


@EndNode

@Node "AR-Preview" "TSMorph.guide/AR-Preview"
@Prev "AR-Postscript"
@Toc "AR"

ARexx script to preview render
==============================

This script is run if the @{"Preview..." Link "CI-men-P-Preview"} or @{"Preview..." Link "I-men-P-Preview"} menu item is
selected. Its purpose is to preview render the image (it can actually do
anything you like).

Before being called the current @{"Settings" Link "Par"} are saved in @{b}T:TSMorph.prefs@{ub}.

It is passed the following parameters:

     @{b}Frame@{ub}    : The frame number to render
     @{b}FileName@{ub} : The file name of the points file

Two examples are included:
     @{"Preview.TSM" ALINK "Rexx/Preview.TSM/Main"} - Render and display 16 grey scale image
     @{"PreAnim.TSM" ALINK "Rexx/PreAnim.TSM/Main"} - Render and display 16 grey scale Anim


@EndNode

@Node "Algorithms" "TSMorph.guide/Algorithms"
@Next "File_Names"
@Prev "AR"
@Toc "Main"

Morphing algorithms
*******************

The morphing algorithm is defined using the parameters @{"MODE" Link "P-MODE"} and @{"DEPTH" Link "P-DEPTH"}
to @{b}TSMorph-render@{ub}.

The basic algorithm is to find 3 points which make a triangle around
the point and morph this triangle between the start and end images.

The @{"DEPTH" Link "P-DEPTH"} parameter controls how many points will be checked to form a
triangle. @{b}0@{ub} means just the closest @{b}3@{ub} points are examined, @{b}1@{ub} the closest
@{b}4@{ub}, @{b}2@{ub} the closest @{b}5@{ub} etc.

The @{"MODE" Link "P-MODE"} parameter controls both which triangle is chosen and what to
do if no surrounding triangle is found.

If @{b}MODE=0 2 4 ... 30@{ub} (i.e. bit 1 not set [do not add 1]) then if no
triangle surrounding the point is found examining the closest points
then the @{b}3@{ub} closest points are used to decide how to morph. Otherwise
the point is assumed to be stationery.

If @{b}MODE=2 3 6 7 ... 30 31@{ub} (i.e. bit 2 set [add 2]) then all the closest
points (the exact number controlled by @{"DEPTH" Link "P-DEPTH"}) are examined to determine
the smallest triangle. Otherwise the first surrounding triangle found is
used.

If @{b}MODE=4 5 6 7 12 ...@{ub} (i.e. bit 3 set [add 4]) then a square algorithm
is used to find the closest points. Otherwise all points are examined.
Although using these MODEs could theoretically make the program run
faster, it seems to generally run slower.

If @{b}MODE=8 9 10 ...@{ub} (i.e. bit 4 set [add 8]) then a Delauany triangle
algorithm is used to find triangles. For these modes the @{"DEPTH" Link "P-DEPTH"} parameter
should normally be set to @{b}0@{ub}. Also floating point calculations are still
done even if @{"INTEGER" Link "P-INTEGER"} is set to @{b}YES@{ub}.

If @{b}MODE=16 17 ...@{ub} (i.e. bit 8 set [add 16]) then the closest triangles
are only calculated once at the start (based on the average of start
and end). This should only be used if the points do not move a lot
between the start and end images. It can speed things up a lot for a
lot of frames. It does not make sense to use this for Animated
Warps/Morphs. This uses a lot of memory:

         (DEPTH + 4) * Image_Width * Image_Height * 4
     
         e.g. 640x512 image, DEPTH=2 uses 7.5 MB (contiguous) memory

Therefore @{b}MODEs 0@{ub} and @{b}1@{ub} should be faster than modes @{b}2@{ub} or @{b}3@{ub}. The @{"DEPTH" Link "P-DEPTH"}
parameter can also have a major effect on the rendering speed.

See @{"Benchmarks" Link "Benchmarks"}.


@EndNode

@Node "Benchmarks" "TSMorph.guide/Benchmarks"
@Toc "Algorithms"

Benchmarks
==========

These benchmarks are based on a Morph provided by "Al Bet Sam That I'm
Not Eloquent, Nancy Colours Eggs" <91016@tayloru.edu> of two 150x150
images with 41 control points.

Times are in seconds to generate the first frame on a 28MHz 68040
running in 32bit fast ram.

                ----------------------------------------------
                | 040 version  | 881 version  | 000 version  | Note all running on a 68040
                ----------------------------------------------
                |INT |   FPU   |INT |   FPU   |INT |   FPU   |   INTEGER=YES/NO/NO
     ---------------------------------------------------------
     |MODE|DEPTH|    |    | AA |    |    | AA |    |    | AA | ANTIALIAS=NO/NO/YES
     ---------------------------------------------------------
     |  0 |  0  | 6.2| 9.1|13.9|    |11.9|    |    |    |    | Shows the effect of DEPTH
     |    |  5  |12.0|15.2|    |    |    |    |    |    |    |
     ---------------------------------------------------------
     |  0 |  2  | 8.4|11.4|17.0| 8.8|14.1|18.5| 9.4|63.8|80.9| On a 68000 with 1MB chip ram, no
     |  1 |     | 8.1|    |    | 8.5|    |    |   x|    |    | fast ram...
     |  2 |     | 8.9|    |    |    |    |    |    |    |    |
     |  4 |     |13.4|    |22.8|13.6|    |23.3|    |    |    | x = 262  (9.4 * 28)
     |  8 |     | 7.6|    |    |    |    |    |    |    |    |
     | 16 |     | 2.8|    |10.7|    |    |12.1|    |    |    |
     | 17 |     | 2.5|    | 8.9| 2.6|    |10.3| 3.2|    |45.5|
     ---------------------------------------------------------
     |  8 |  0  | 6.4|    |    |    |    |    |    |    |    |
     ---------------------------------------------------------
     | 15 |  0  | 7.1|    |    |    |    |    |    |    |    |
     ---------------------------------------------------------
     | 16 |  0  | 1.7| 4.6| 9.5| 1.7| 6.7|10.6| 2.5|56.0|    |
     ---------------------------------------------------------


@EndNode

@Node "File_Names" "TSMorph.guide/File_Names"
@Next "Errors"
@Prev "Algorithms"
@Toc "Main"

File naming
***********

File names can include the frame number.

The format of the frame number in the file name is specified using the
following formats:

     @{b}%ld@{ub}     : Number left justified e.g.  '1','2',..,'10',..,'123',..
     @{b}%3ld@{ub}    : Number right justified e.g. '  1','  2',..,' 10',..,'123',..
     @{b}%03ld@{ub}   : Number right justified e.g. '001','002',..,'010',..,'123',..

Where the number can be changed e.g.

     @{b}pic.%04ld@{ub}   for Imagine 2.0 produced files
     @{b}pic%03ld@{ub}    for Vista produced files
     @{b}name%ld@{ub}     for files to run through mpeg


@EndNode

@Node "Errors" "TSMorph.guide/Errors"
@Next "Bugs"
@Prev "File_Names"
@Toc "Main"

Error Messages
**************

The following messages can be displayed in an @{"Error Requester" Link "Req-Error"}.


 @{" Both Images must be the same size       " Link "Err-Size"}         
 @{" Unable to Open Grid Requester           " Link "Err-OpenGrid"}             
 @{" Both X Cells and Y Cells must be > 0    " Link "Err-Grid0"}          
 @{" Out of memory for points                " Link "Err-MemoryPoints"}                 
 @{" No ILBM.BMHD chunk                      " Link "Err-IFFBMHD"}            
 @{" Failed to allocate raster               " Link "Err-IFFRaster"}              
 @{" No ILBM.BODY chunk                      " Link "Err-IFFBODY"}            
 @{" Not an ILBM                             " Link "Err-IFFILBM"}            
 @{" Clipboard open failed                   " Link "Err-IFFCLIP"}            
 @{" xxxx; File open failed                  " Link "Err-IFFFileS"}             
 @{" Parsing error; no top chunk             " Link "Err-IFFTop"}           
 @{" Not enough memory                       " Link "Err-IFFMemory"}              
 @{" Failure opening TSMorph Window          " Link "Err-OpenTSMorph"}                
 @{" Failure setting up screen               " Link "Err-SetupScreen"}                
 @{" Can not Open xxxx.library(n)            " Link "Err-Library"}            
 @{" Unable to Allocate FileRequest          " Link "Err-FileReq"}            
 @{" Unable to Create Window Message Port    " Link "Err-WPort"}          
 @{" Can not Open input.device               " Link "Err-IDevice"}            
 @{" Image smaller than points               " Link "Err-ISmall"}           
 @{" Images different sizes                  " Link "Err-IDifferent"}               
 @{" Unable to Allocate Zoom raster          " Link "Err-ZRaster"}            
 @{" Unable to SetMenuStrip                  " Link "Err-Menu"}         
 @{" Unable to OpenWindowTags                " Link "Err-OpenWindow"}               
 @{" Unable to AllocMem for Filename         " Link "Err-MemFile"}            
 @{" Unable to Allocate xxxx Gadget          " Link "Err-AllocGadget"}                
 @{" Unable to Allocate xxxx Image           " Link "Err-AllocImage"}               
 @{" Failure loading Image 'xxxx'            " Link "Err-LoadImage"}              
 @{" Unable to AllocIFF                      " Link "Err-AllocIFF"}             
 @{" Unable to AllocMem for ILBMInfo         " Link "Err-AllocILBM"}              
 @{" Unable to GetScreenDrawInfo             " Link "Err-GetDRI"}           
 @{" Unable to LockPubScreen(xxxx)           " Link "Err-LockScreen"}               
 @{" Invalid file format - Line 'xxxx'       " Link "Err-FileFormat"}               
 @{" Images are too small                    " Link "Err-TooSmall"}             
 @{" Point out of range - Line 'xxxx'        " Link "Err-Range"}          
 @{" Out of memory for points                " Link "Err-MemPoints"}              
 @{" Invalid point link - Line 'xxxx'        " Link "Err-InvalidLink"}                
 @{" Error closing file 'xxxx'               " Link "Err-CloseFile"}              
 @{" Error opening file 'xxxx'               " Link "Err-OpenFile"}             
 @{" Error writing to 'xxxx'                 " Link "Err-WriteFile"}              
 @{" Point already linked to 16 points       " Link "Err-4Points"}            
 @{" Point not linked                        " Link "Err-NotLinked"}              
 @{" Cannot link point to itself             " Link "Err-LinkSelf"}             
 @{" Points already linked                   " Link "Err-Linked"}           
 @{" Cannot unlink point from itself         " Link "Err-UnlinkSelf"}               
 @{" Error no memory for new point           " Link "Err-MemNewPoint"}                
 @{" Unable to Open xxxx.library(n)          " Link "Err-LibraryR"}             
 @{" Error saving file 'xxxx'                " Link "Err-Saving"}           
 @{" Error AllocVec for output               " Link "Err-AllocVec"}             
 @{" Error Opening points file               " Link "Err-OpenPoints"}               
 @{" Error opening progress window           " Link "Err-Progress"}             
 @{" Unable to allocate memory for bitmap    " Link "Err-AllocPlanes"}                
 @{" Image must be 24 bit 'xxxx'             " Link "Err-24"}       
 @{" Error loading 'xxxx'                    " Link "Err-Load"}         
 @{" Size does not match image - Line 'xxxx' " Link "Err-SizeMatch"}              
 @{" Out of memory for points                " Link "Err-MemPointsR"}               
 @{" Must have at least 3 points             " Link "Err-3Points"}            
 @{" Error sending ARexx message - 'xxxx'    " Link "Err-ARexx"}          
 @{" Assuming version 1.0 file format        " Link "Err-OldFormat"}              
 @{" Must have at least one frame            " Link "Err-OneFrame"}             
 @{" Frames must all be the same size        " Link "Err-AllSize"}            
 @{" Failure - yyyy - loading 'xxxx'         " Link "Err-OpalVision"}               
 @{" Error Saving Settings 'xxxx'            " Link "Err-SaveS"}          
 @{" Error Loading Settings 'xxxx'           " Link "Err-LoadS"}          
 @{" No opal.library                         " Link "Err-NoOpal"}           
 @{" File does not exist 'xxxx'              " Link "Err-NoFile"}           
 @{" Error opening screen                    " Link "Err-OScreen"}            
 @{" Unable to get DrawInfo                  " Link "Err-DrawI"}          
 @{" Unable to lock Workbench                " Link "Err-LockW"}          
 @{" Invalid screen mode xxxx                " Link "Err-SMode"}          
 @{" TSMorph is attempting to close this ... " Link "Err-CScreen"} 


@EndNode

@Node "Err-Size" "TSMorph.guide/Err-Size"
@Next "Err-OpenGrid"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Both Images must be the same size
=========================================

This message should never be displayed. @{"Images different sizes" Link "Err-IDifferent"} should
be displayed instead.

Resolution - None required.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-OpenGrid" "TSMorph.guide/Err-OpenGrid"
@Next "Err-Grid0"
@Prev "Err-Size"
@Toc "Errors"

Unable to Open Grid Requester
=============================

@{b}TSMorph@{ub} is unable to open the @{"Add Grid" Link "Req-Add_Grid"} requester. The normal reason
would be lack of memory.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-Grid0" "TSMorph.guide/Err-Grid0"
@Next "Err-MemoryPoints"
@Prev "Err-OpenGrid"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Both X Cells and Y Cells must be > 0
============================================

This message is displayed if the @{"Add Grid" Link "Req-Add_Grid"} requester is used and either
the @{"X Cells" Link "Req-Add_Grid-gad-X_Cells"} or @{"Y Cells" Link "Req-Add_Grid-gad-Y_Cells"} is set to @{b}0@{ub}. The minimum allowed value is @{b}1@{ub}.

Resolution - Input at least @{b}1@{ub} in both gadgets, or @{"cancel" Link "Req-Add_Grid-gad-Cancel"} the requester.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-MemoryPoints" "TSMorph.guide/Err-MemoryPoints"
@Next "Err-IFFBMHD"
@Prev "Err-Grid0"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Out of memory for points
================================

This message is displayed after the @{"Add Grid" Link "Req-Add_Grid"} requester has been used
and points and lines are being added to the images. Insufficient memory
is available.

Resolution - Since it is possible that some of the points have been
added to the images then you may wish to use the @{"New Points" Link "CI-men-P-New"} menu item
to delete all points. Then free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-IFFBMHD" "TSMorph.guide/Err-IFFBMHD"
@Next "Err-IFFRaster"
@Prev "Err-MemoryPoints"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - No ILBM.BMHD chunk
==========================

The Image being loaded has no BMHD chunk.

Resolution - Specify the name of a correct ILBM image.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-IFFRaster" "TSMorph.guide/Err-IFFRaster"
@Next "Err-IFFBODY"
@Prev "Err-IFFBMHD"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Failed to allocate raster
=================================

There is insufficient memory to load the ILBM image.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-IFFBODY" "TSMorph.guide/Err-IFFBODY"
@Next "Err-IFFILBM"
@Prev "Err-IFFRaster"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - No ILBM.BODY chunk
==========================

The Image being loaded has no BODY chunk.

Resolution - Specify the name of a correct ILBM image.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-IFFILBM" "TSMorph.guide/Err-IFFILBM"
@Next "Err-IFFCLIP"
@Prev "Err-IFFBODY"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Not an ILBM
===================

The Image being loaded is not and ILBM file.

Resolution - Specify the name of a correct ILBM image.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-IFFCLIP" "TSMorph.guide/Err-IFFCLIP"
@Next "Err-IFFFileS"
@Prev "Err-IFFILBM"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Clipboard open failed
=============================

The program is unable to open the specified clipboard.

Resolution - Retry with the correct clipboard number, or use a
different file name.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-IFFFileS" "TSMorph.guide/Err-IFFFileS"
@Next "Err-IFFTop"
@Prev "Err-IFFCLIP"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - @{i}xxxx@{ui}; File open failed
==============================

File @{i}xxxx@{ui} can not be successfully opened. The file does not exist (if
trying to read), is already in use, or the filename is invalid.

Resolution - Retry with a valid file name.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-IFFTop" "TSMorph.guide/Err-IFFTop"
@Next "Err-IFFMemory"
@Prev "Err-IFFFileS"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Parsing error; no top chunk
===================================

This is a technical error which should never occur.

Resolution - Unknown.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-IFFMemory" "TSMorph.guide/Err-IFFMemory"
@Next "Err-OpenTSMorph"
@Prev "Err-IFFTop"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Not enough memory
=========================

There is insufficient memory to save or load the IFF ILBM file.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-OpenTSMorph" "TSMorph.guide/Err-OpenTSMorph"
@Next "Err-SetupScreen"
@Prev "Err-IFFMemory"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Failure opening TSMorph Window
======================================

The @{"Information Window" Link "Info"} window could not be opened. There is probably
insufficient memory.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-SetupScreen" "TSMorph.guide/Err-SetupScreen"
@Next "Err-Library"
@Prev "Err-OpenTSMorph"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Failure setting up screen
=================================

The @{"Information Window" Link "Info"} window could not be opened. Either the
@{"Public Screen" Link "P-PUBSCREEN"} is not open or there is insufficient memory.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry, or correct the @{"PUBSCREEN" Link "P-PUBSCREEN"}
parameter.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-Library" "TSMorph.guide/Err-Library"
@Next "Err-FileReq"
@Prev "Err-SetupScreen"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Can not Open @{i}xxxx@{ui}.library(@{i}n@{ui})
====================================

The library @{i}xxxx@{ui} version number @{i}n@{ui} could not be opened. See @{"Requirements" Link "Requirements"}
for a list of libraries required. It could just be a lack of memory.

Resolution - Ensure you are running at least version 2.04 of the
operating system, or free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-FileReq" "TSMorph.guide/Err-FileReq"
@Next "Err-WPort"
@Prev "Err-Library"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Unable to Allocate FileRequest
======================================

Insufficient memory is available.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-WPort" "TSMorph.guide/Err-WPort"
@Next "Err-IDevice"
@Prev "Err-FileReq"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Unable to Create Window Message Port
============================================

Insufficient memory is available.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-IDevice" "TSMorph.guide/Err-IDevice"
@Next "Err-ISmall"
@Prev "Err-WPort"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Can not Open input.device
=================================

Insufficient memory is available.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-ISmall" "TSMorph.guide/Err-ISmall"
@Next "Err-IDifferent"
@Prev "Err-IDevice"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Image smaller than points
=================================

The image trying to be loaded is smaller than the points already
defined.

Resolution - Load a larger image, or select the @{"New" Link "I-men-P-New"} menu item and
restart.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-IDifferent" "TSMorph.guide/Err-IDifferent"
@Next "Err-ZRaster"
@Prev "Err-ISmall"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Images different sizes
==============================

This can be displayed when opening the second image in @{b}TSMorph@{ub}. Both
images must have the same horizontal and vertical resolutions. The image
depths can be different.

Resolution - Either use a different pair of images, or change the size
of one of the images using some image-processing program.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-ZRaster" "TSMorph.guide/Err-ZRaster"
@Next "Err-Menu"
@Prev "Err-IDifferent"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Unable to Allocate Zoom raster
======================================

Insufficient memory is available.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry. If you still do not have
enough memory then rerun specifying @{"ZOOM=OFF" Link "P-ZOOM"} as a parameter.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-Menu" "TSMorph.guide/Err-Menu"
@Next "Err-OpenWindow"
@Prev "Err-ZRaster"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Unable to SetMenuStrip
==============================

Insufficient memory is available.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-OpenWindow" "TSMorph.guide/Err-OpenWindow"
@Next "Err-MemFile"
@Prev "Err-Menu"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Unable to OpenWindowTags
================================

Insufficient memory is available.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-MemFile" "TSMorph.guide/Err-MemFile"
@Next "Err-AllocGadget"
@Prev "Err-OpenWindow"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Unable to AllocMem for Filename
=======================================

Insufficient memory is available.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-AllocGadget" "TSMorph.guide/Err-AllocGadget"
@Next "Err-AllocImage"
@Prev "Err-MemFile"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Unable to Allocate @{i}xxxx@{ui} Gadget
======================================

Insufficient memory is available.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-AllocImage" "TSMorph.guide/Err-AllocImage"
@Next "Err-LoadImage"
@Prev "Err-AllocGadget"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Unable to Allocate @{i}xxxx@{ui} Image
=====================================

Insufficient memory is available.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-LoadImage" "TSMorph.guide/Err-LoadImage"
@Next "Err-AllocIFF"
@Prev "Err-AllocImage"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Failure loading Image '@{i}xxxx@{ui}'
====================================

There was an error loading the image @{i}xxxx@{ui}. Another error message should
previously have been displayed.

Resolution - See previous error message.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-AllocIFF" "TSMorph.guide/Err-AllocIFF"
@Next "Err-AllocILBM"
@Prev "Err-LoadImage"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Unable to AllocIFF
==========================

Insufficient memory is available.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-AllocILBM" "TSMorph.guide/Err-AllocILBM"
@Next "Err-GetDRI"
@Prev "Err-AllocIFF"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Unable to AllocMem for ILBMInfo
=======================================

Insufficient memory is available.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-GetDRI" "TSMorph.guide/Err-GetDRI"
@Next "Err-LockScreen"
@Prev "Err-AllocILBM"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Unable to GetScreenDrawInfo
===================================

Insufficient memory is available.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-LockScreen" "TSMorph.guide/Err-LockScreen"
@Next "Err-FileFormat"
@Prev "Err-GetDRI"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Unable to LockPubScreen(@{i}xxxx@{ui})
=====================================

Either the @{"Public Screen" Link "P-PUBSCREEN"} is not open or there is insufficient memory.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry, or correct the @{"PUBSCREEN" Link "P-PUBSCREEN"}
parameter.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-FileFormat" "TSMorph.guide/Err-FileFormat"
@Next "Err-TooSmall"
@Prev "Err-LockScreen"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Invalid file format - Line '@{i}xxxx@{ui}'
=========================================

The points file being loaded is in an incorrect @{"Format" Link "File_Format"} or is not a
points file.

Resolution - Specify a correct points file or manually edit the file
and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-TooSmall" "TSMorph.guide/Err-TooSmall"
@Next "Err-Range"
@Prev "Err-FileFormat"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Images are too small
============================

The images specified in the input file are too small.

Resolution - Either edit the input file - See @{"Format" Link "File_Format"}, or select the @{"New" Link "I-men-P-New"}
menu item and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-Range" "TSMorph.guide/Err-Range"
@Next "Err-MemPoints"
@Prev "Err-TooSmall"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Point out of range - Line '@{i}xxxx@{ui}'
========================================

The point coordinates specified in the input file is larger than the
image size.

Resolution - Manually edit the input file - See @{"Format" Link "File_Format"} and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-MemPoints" "TSMorph.guide/Err-MemPoints"
@Next "Err-InvalidLink"
@Prev "Err-Range"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Out of memory for points
================================

Insufficient memory is available.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry after selecting either @{"New" Link "I-men-P-New"}
or @{"New Points" Link "CI-men-P-New"} to delete existing points.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-InvalidLink" "TSMorph.guide/Err-InvalidLink"
@Next "Err-CloseFile"
@Prev "Err-MemPoints"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Invalid point link - Line '@{i}xxxx@{ui}'
========================================

The points linking specified in the input file is invalid.

Resolution - Manually edit the input file - See @{"Format" Link "File_Format"} and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-CloseFile" "TSMorph.guide/Err-CloseFile"
@Next "Err-OpenFile"
@Prev "Err-InvalidLink"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Error closing file '@{i}xxxx@{ui}'
=================================

The file @{i}xxxx@{ui} could not be successfully closed. The disc may be full.

Resolution - If saving then save the file to a different disk or free up
some disk space and retry with another name. The original file may not
be accessible until after a reboot.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-OpenFile" "TSMorph.guide/Err-OpenFile"
@Next "Err-WriteFile"
@Prev "Err-CloseFile"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Error opening file '@{i}xxxx@{ui}'
=================================

The file @{i}xxxx@{ui} could not be opened. The file does not exist (when
reading), the name is invalid, the file is already in use, or the disk
is write protected.

Resolution - Use a different file name or allow the disk to be written
to.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-WriteFile" "TSMorph.guide/Err-WriteFile"
@Next "Err-4Points"
@Prev "Err-OpenFile"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Error writing to '@{i}xxxx@{ui}'
===============================

The file @{i}xxxx@{ui} could not be successfully written to. The disc may be
full. The file has not been successfully saved.

Resolution - Save the file to a different disk or free up some disk
space and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-4Points" "TSMorph.guide/Err-4Points"
@Next "Err-NotLinked"
@Prev "Err-WriteFile"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Point already linked to 16 points
=========================================

Any point can only be @{"linked" Link "EMode-Link"} to up to 16 other points. @{b}Note:@{ub} the links
are only for clarity and do not effect the rendering process.

Resolution - @{"Unlink" Link "EMode-Unlink"} the current point from some other point and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-NotLinked" "TSMorph.guide/Err-NotLinked"
@Next "Err-LinkSelf"
@Prev "Err-4Points"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Point not linked
========================

The points just selected are not currently @{"linked" Link "EMode-Link"} and cannot therefore
be @{"unlinked" Link "EMode-Unlink"}.

Resolution - None required.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-LinkSelf" "TSMorph.guide/Err-LinkSelf"
@Next "Err-Linked"
@Prev "Err-NotLinked"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Cannot link point to itself
===================================

A point can not be @{"Linked" Link "EMode-Link"} to itself.

Resolution - Select another point to link to.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-Linked" "TSMorph.guide/Err-Linked"
@Next "Err-UnlinkSelf"
@Prev "Err-LinkSelf"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Points already linked
=============================

The points you are trying to @{"link" Link "EMode-Link"} are already linked.

Resolution - None required.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-UnlinkSelf" "TSMorph.guide/Err-UnlinkSelf"
@Next "Err-MemNewPoint"
@Prev "Err-Linked"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Cannot unlink point from itself
=======================================

A point can not be @{"unlinked" Link "EMode-Unlink"} from itself.

Resolution - Select another point to unlink from.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-MemNewPoint" "TSMorph.guide/Err-MemNewPoint"
@Next "Err-LibraryR"
@Prev "Err-UnlinkSelf"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Error no memory for new point
=====================================

There is no memory to add the new point.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-LibraryR" "TSMorph.guide/Err-LibraryR"
@Next "Err-Saving"
@Prev "Err-MemNewPoint"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Unable to Open @{i}xxxx@{ui}.library(@{i}n@{ui})
======================================

The library @{i}xxxx@{ui} version number @{i}n@{ui} could not be opened. See @{"Requirements" Link "Requirements"}
for a list of libraries required. It could just be a lack of memory.

Resolution - Ensure you are running at least version 2.04 of the
operating system, or free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-Saving" "TSMorph.guide/Err-Saving"
@Next "Err-AllocVec"
@Prev "Err-LibraryR"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Error saving file '@{i}xxxx@{ui}'
================================

Some error occurred saving the IFF ILBM output file. Another error
requester may have previously appeared. Alternatively there could be a
lack of memory. This error is also displayed when trying to save DCTV
images in an invalid size.

Resolution - See the previous error message, or free up some memory and
retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-AllocVec" "TSMorph.guide/Err-AllocVec"
@Next "Err-OpenPoints"
@Prev "Err-Saving"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Error AllocVec for output
=================================

Insufficient memory is available.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-OpenPoints" "TSMorph.guide/Err-OpenPoints"
@Next "Err-Progress"
@Prev "Err-AllocVec"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Error Opening points file
=================================

The input file specified to @{b}TSMorph-render@{ub} does not exist or is in an
invalid @{"format" Link "File_Format"}.

Resolution - Either specify a valid input file, or manually edit the
points file.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-Progress" "TSMorph.guide/Err-Progress"
@Next "Err-AllocPlanes"
@Prev "Err-OpenPoints"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Error opening progress window
=====================================

Some error occurred opening the @{"Progress" Link "Req-Progress"} requester in @{b}TSMorph-render@{ub}.
Probably a lack of memory, or the @{"PUBSCREENR" Link "P-PUBSCREENR"} parameter specifies a not
open public screen name.

Resolution - Free up some memory or correct the parameter and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-AllocPlanes" "TSMorph.guide/Err-AllocPlanes"
@Next "Err-24"
@Prev "Err-Progress"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Unable to allocate memory for bitmap
============================================

Insufficient memory is available for some bitmap planes.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-24" "TSMorph.guide/Err-24"
@Next "Err-Load"
@Prev "Err-AllocPlanes"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Image must be 24 bit '@{i}xxxx@{ui}'
===================================

The image @{i}xxxx@{ui} being loaded by @{b}TSMorph-render@{ub} is not a 24 bit image.
Only 24 bit ILBM images can be rendered.

This is an obsolete message which should not appear.

Resolution - Use @{b}TSMorph@{ub} to specify a valid 24 bit ILBM image.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-Load" "TSMorph.guide/Err-Load"
@Next "Err-SizeMatch"
@Prev "Err-24"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Error loading '@{i}xxxx@{ui}'
============================

The image @{i}xxxx@{ui} being loaded by @{b}TSMorph-render@{ub} could not be loaded. A
previous error requester could have appeared. The file name could be
invalid.

Resolution - See the previous error message.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-SizeMatch" "TSMorph.guide/Err-SizeMatch"
@Next "Err-MemPointsR"
@Prev "Err-Load"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Size does not match image - Line '@{i}xxxx@{ui}'
===============================================

The points file being loaded - See @{"File Format" Link "File_Format"} - has an image size
specified which does not match the image being loaded.

Resolution - Change the image size, manually edit the input file, or
respecify the image name using @{b}TSMorph@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-MemPointsR" "TSMorph.guide/Err-MemPointsR"
@Next "Err-3Points"
@Prev "Err-SizeMatch"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Out of memory for points
================================

Insufficient memory is available.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-3Points" "TSMorph.guide/Err-3Points"
@Next "Err-ARexx"
@Prev "Err-MemPointsR"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Must have at least 3 points
===================================

In order to correctly render an image at least 3 points must be defined.

Resolution - Use @{b}TSMorph@{ub} to define at least 3 points - e.g. in 3 of the
corners.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-ARexx" "TSMorph.guide/Err-ARexx"
@Next "Err-OldFormat"
@Prev "Err-3Points"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Error sending ARexx message - '@{i}xxxx@{ui}'
============================================

@{b}TSMorph-render@{ub} or @{b}TSMorph@{ub} has had a problem sending the @{"ARexx" Link "AR"} message.
ARexx may not be running, or the script may not exist or have errors.

Resolution - Ensure ARexx is running, check the scripts - See parameters
@{"PRESCRIPT" Link "P-PRESCRIPT"}, @{"POSTSCRIPT" Link "P-POSTSCRIPT"} and @{"LOADSCRIPT" Link "P-LOADSCRIPT"}, or @{"PREVIEW" Link "P-PREVIEW"} - exist and have TSM
as a suffix.

If the above is OK then use @{b}TCO@{ub} and @{b}TS@{ub} to interactively trace the
script.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-OldFormat" "TSMorph.guide/Err-OldFormat"
@Next "Err-OneFrame"
@Prev "Err-ARexx"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Assuming version 1.0 file format
========================================

The current version of the @{"File Format" Link "File_Format"} has a header record. This error
is saying no header is present, it is assumed that the file is in an
old format.

Resolution - Select OK to continue. Load and Save in @{b}TSMorph@{ub} to save in
the new format if required.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-OneFrame" "TSMorph.guide/Err-OneFrame"
@Next "Err-AllSize"
@Prev "Err-OldFormat"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Must have at least one frame
====================================

This is displayed when trying to edit points on an Animated Morph/Warp
when the number of frames is @{b}0@{ub}.

Resolution - Set the number of @{"frames" Link "I-gad-Frames"} to at least @{b}1@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-AllSize" "TSMorph.guide/Err-AllSize"
@Next "Err-OpalVision"
@Prev "Err-OneFrame"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Frames must all be the same size
========================================

This is displayed when trying to change to a different frame. The size
of all input images must be the same.

Resolution - Ensure all input images are the same size.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-OpalVision" "TSMorph.guide/Err-OpalVision"
@Next "Err-SaveS"
@Prev "Err-AllSize"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Failure - @{i}yyyy@{ui} - loading '@{i}xxxx@{ui}'
=======================================

@{b}opal.library@{ub} had a problem loading image @{i}xxxx@{ui}.

Resolution - @{i}yyyy@{ui} should describe the problem.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-SaveS" "TSMorph.guide/Err-SaveS"
@Next "Err-LoadS"
@Prev "Err-OpalVision"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Error Saving Settings '@{i}xxxx@{ui}'
====================================

This message is displayed when @{b}TSMorph@{ub} has been unable to save @{"settings" Link "Par"}
in the named file. If @{"KEEPSETTINGS" Link "P-KEEPSETTINGS"} is set to @{b}YES@{ub} then settings are
saved in @{b}ENV:TSMorph/TSMorph.prefs@{ub} when the program is quit.

Resolution - Supply a correct filename, set @{b}KEEPSETTINGS@{ub} to @{b}NO@{ub}, or
create the directory @{b}ENV:TSMorph@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "Err-LoadS" "TSMorph.guide/Err-LoadS"
@Next "Err-NoOpal"
@Prev "Err-SaveS"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Error Loading Settings '@{i}xxxx@{ui}'
=====================================

@{b}TSMorph@{ub} has had a problem loading the specified file. The file probably
does not exist.

Resolution - Specify a correct file name


@EndNode

@Node "Err-NoOpal" "TSMorph.guide/Err-NoOpal"
@Next "Err-NoFile"
@Prev "Err-LoadS"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - No @{b}opal.library@{ub}
=======================

@{b}TSMorph@{ub} or @{b}TSMorph-render@{ub} is trying to load an image using @{b}opal.library@{ub}
but it could not be opened.

Resolution - For @{b}TSMorph@{ub} - If you do not have @{b}opal.library@{ub} do not
specify @{"OPENMODE=OPAL" Link "P-OPENMODE"}. If you are not specifying this then the image
you are trying to load must be in a format which @{b}TSMorph@{ub} does not
understand (this may be some unsupported JPEG variant).

For @{b}TSMorph-render@{ub} - This is trying to load some unsupported image
format.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-NoFile" "TSMorph.guide/Err-NoFile"
@Next "Err-OScreen"
@Prev "Err-NoOpal"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - File does not exist '@{i}xxxx@{ui}'
==================================

@{b}TSMorph@{ub} is trying to load an image from a file which does not exist or
is inaccessible.

Resolution - Specify a valid file name.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-OScreen" "TSMorph.guide/Err-OScreen"
@Next "Err-DrawI"
@Prev "Err-NoFile"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Error opening screen
============================

@{b}TSMorph@{ub} has been unable to open the requested screen. This could be
because the @{"CUSTOMDEPTH" Link "P-CUSTOMDEPTH"} is too great for the @{"CUSTOMMODE" Link "P-CUSTOMMODE"}, there is not
enough memory, or some other related reason.

Resolution - Check you have enough memory, make sure the screen depth
is OK for the screen mode.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-DrawI" "TSMorph.guide/Err-DrawI"
@Next "Err-LockW"
@Prev "Err-OScreen"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Unable to get DrawInfo
==============================

@{b}TSMorph@{ub} has been unable to obtain some information from the Workbench,
probably due to lack of memory.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-LockW" "TSMorph.guide/Err-LockW"
@Next "Err-SMode"
@Prev "Err-DrawI"
@Toc "Errors"

Error - Unable to lock Workbench
================================

@{b}TSMorph@{ub} has been unable to obtain some information from the Workbench,
probably due to lack of memory.

Resolution - Free up some memory and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-SMode" "TSMorph.guide/Err-SMode"
@Next "Err-CScreen"
@Prev "Err-LockW"
@Toc "Errors"

Invalid screen mode @{i}xxxx@{ui}
========================

The screen mode specified by @{"CUSTOMMODE" Link "P-CUSTOMMODE"} is not a valid screen mode.

Resolution - Check the screen mode against the list show in the
preferences screen mode requester.


@EndNode

@Node "Err-CScreen" "TSMorph.guide/Err-CScreen"
@Prev "Err-SMode"
@Toc "Errors"

TSMorph is attempting to close this ...
=======================================

TSMorph is trying to close the @{"Public Screen" Link "P-PUBSCREEN"} that it opened but is
unable to as there are locks (probably open windows) on the screen.

Resolution - Close all other open windows on the screen and retry.


@EndNode

@Node "Bugs" "TSMorph.guide/Bugs"
@Next "Hard-Software"
@Prev "Errors"
@Toc "Main"

Known (and unknown errors)
**************************

   @{b}*@{ub} Known Problems

        @{b}*@{ub} Unsaved project does not check that gadgets really have been
          edited.

        @{b}*@{ub} This guide sometimes has very long lines. Also @{b}bold@{ub} items
          following @{b}*@{ub} are followed by too many spaces.  This appears to
          be due to a problem with MakeInfo, menus and lists.

        @{b}*@{ub} This guide may not look correct when using amigaguide.library
          versions before 40. This will not be fixed.

        @{b}*@{ub} Fails to do anything if run on less than 2.04 (could display
          a message). This is unlikely to be fixed.

        @{b}*@{ub} Progress gadgets do not look to good using 2.04. They do look
          OK when using 3.0+. This will not be fixed.

        @{b}*@{ub} 24 bit ILBMs are loaded into Chip memory. If you do not have
          enough, then convert the input images to PPM or JPEG first.
          (Thanks to Jamie Cope).

        @{b}*@{ub} Sizing EGS windows from the top or left may corrupt the
          display. I believe this an EGS problem.

   @{b}*@{ub} Unknown Problems?

        @{b}*@{ub} Image validation requires tidying up - especially with anim
          morphs/warps.

        @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}TSMorph@{ub} and @{b}TSMorph-render@{ub} @{b}may@{ub} not release all memory.

        @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}TSMorph-prefs@{ub} has not been well tested.

        @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}TSMorph@{ub} may open zoomed large windows with corruption.

        @{b}*@{ub} Width and Height in the parameter file may not be correctly
          set and require manual editing.

Please report any other bugs by EMail to mark@topic.demon.co.uk or
mpaddock@cix.compulink.co.uk.


@EndNode

@Node "Hard-Software" "TSMorph.guide/Hard-Software"
@Next "History"
@Prev "Bugs"
@Toc "Main"

Hardware and Software used in development
*****************************************

   @{b}*@{ub} HSPascal            Editor.

   @{b}*@{ub} SAS C               Code.

   @{b}*@{ub} GadToolsBox         Info, Add Grid and Progress Windows.
     GadToolsBox is © Copyright 1991,92 Jaba Development.

   @{b}*@{ub} DPaint              Control Window gadgets/Pointers.

   @{b}*@{ub} Workbench 2.04      GUI.

   @{b}*@{ub} MakeInfo            Documentation.

